obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (3130)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes `1. 22nd July, 1950, vide Notification No. S.R.O. 124, dated 22nd July, see Gazette of India, 1950, Part II, sec. 4.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=3130&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Air Force Act, 1950.`
  line
  line `(2) It shall come into force on such date^1`
  line `as the Central Government may by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (3131)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title `Persons subject to this Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 62 of 1952, s. 35, for clause (c) (w.e.f. 15-8-1955).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=3131&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `The following persons shall be subject to this Act wherever they`
  line `may be, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) officers and warrant officers of the Air Force;`
  line
  line `(b) persons enrolled under this Act;`
  line
  line `^1[(c) persons belonging to the Regular Air Force Reserve or the Air Defence Reserve or the`
  line `Auxiliary Air Force, in the circumstances specified in section 26 of the Reserve and Auxiliary Air`
  line `Forces Act, 1952 (62 of 1952);]`
  line
  line `(d) persons not otherwise subject to air force law, who, on active service, in camp, on the march,`
  line `or at any frontier post specified by the Central Government by notification in this behalf, are`
  line `employed by, or are in the service of, or are followers of, or accompany any portion of the Air Force.`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (3132)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Termination of application of the Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=3132&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `Every person subject to this Act under clauses (a) to (c)`
  line `of section 2 shall remain so subject until duly retired, discharged, released, removed, dismissed or`
  line `cashiered from the service.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (3133)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=3133&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires.`
  line
  line `(i) "active service", as applied to a person subject to this Act, means the time during which such`
  line person--
  line
  line `(a) is attached to, or forms part of a force which is engaged in operations against an enemy,`
  line or
  line
  line `(b) is engaged in air force operations in, or is on the line of march to, a country or place`
  line `wholly or partly occupied by an enemy, or`
  line
  line `(c) is attached to, or forms part of, a force which is in military occupation of any foreign`
  line country;
  line
  line `(ii) "aircraft includes" aeroplanes, balloons, lite balloons, airships, gliders or other machines for`
  line flying;
  line
  line `(iii) "aircraft material" includes any engines, fittings, guns, gear, instruments or apparatus for use`
  line `in connection with aircraft, and any of its components and accessories and petrol oil, and any other`
  line `substance used for providing motive power for planes;`
  line
  line `(iv) "Air Force" means officers and airmen who by their commission, warrant, terms of`
  line `enrolment or otherwise, are liable to render continuously for a term air force service to the Union in`
  line `every part of the world or any specified part of the world, including persons belonging to^1 [any Air`
  line `Force Reserve or the Auxiliary Air Force], when called out on permanent service;`
  line
  line `(v) "Air force custody" means the arrest or confinement of a person according to the usages of the`
  line `service and includes military or naval custody;`
  line
  line `(vi) "Air Force law" means the law enacted by this Act and the rules made thereunder and`
  line `includes the usages of the service;`
  line
  line `(vii) "Air Force reward" includes any gratuity or annuity for long service or good conduct, badge`
  line `pay or pension, and any other Air Force pecuniary reward;`
  line
  line `(viii) "airman" means any person subject to this Act other than an officer;`
  line
  line `(ix) "air officer" means any officer of the Air Force above the rank of group captain;`
  line
  line `(x) "air signal" means any signal intended for the guidance of aircraft, whether given by flag,`
  line `ground signal, light, wind indicator or in any manner whatsoever;`
  line
  line `(xi) "Chief Legal Adviser" means a person appointed as such by^2`
  line `the Chief of the Air staff to`
  line `give advice on matters relating to air force law and to perform such other duties of a legal character as`
  line `may arise in connection therewith;`
  line
  line `(xii) "civil offence" means an offence which is triable by a criminal court;`
  line
  line `(xiii) "civil prison" means any jail or place used for the detention of any criminal prisoner under`
  line `the Prisons Act, 1894 (9 of 1894), or under any other law for the time being in force;`
  line
  line ^3
  line `[(xiv) "Chief of the Air Staff" means the officer commanding the Air Force;]`
  line
  line `(xv) "commanding officer" used in relation to a person subject to this Act, means the officer for`
  line `the time being in command of the unit or detachment to which such person belongs or is attached;`
  line
  line `(xvi) "court-martial" means a court-martial held under this Act;`
  line
  line `(xvii) "criminal court" means a court of ordinary criminal justice in any part of India,^4`
  line `* * * * *;`
  line
  line `(xviii) "enemy" includes all armed mutineers, armed rebels, armed rioters, pirates and any person`
  line `in arms against whom it is the duty of any person subject to air force law to act;`
  line
  line `(xix) "the Forces" means the regular Army, Navy and Air Force or any part of any one or more of`
  line them;
  line
  line `(xx) "non-commissioned officer" means a person holding a non-commissioned rank or an acting`
  line `non-commissioned rank in the Air Force, and includes any person holding a non-commissioned rank`
  line `or an acting non-commissioned rank in ^5[any Air Force Reserve or the Auxiliary Air Force] when`
  line `subject to this Act;`
  line
  line `(xxi) "notification" means a notification published in the Official Gazette;`
  line
  line `(xxii) "offence" means any act or omission punishable under this Act, and includes a civil`
  line `offence, as hereinbefore defined;`
  line
  line `(xxiii) "officer" means a person commissioned, gazetted or in pay as an officer in the Air Force,`
  line `and includes--`
  line
  line `(a) an officer of ^5[any Air Force Reserve or the Auxiliary Air Force] who is for the time being`
  line `subject to this Act;`
  line
  line `(b) in relation to a person subject to this Act when serving under such conditions as may be`
  line `prescribed, an officer of the regular Army or the Navy,`
  line
  line `but does not include a junior commissioned officer, warrant officer, petty officer or non-commissioned`
  line officer;
  line
  line `(xxiv) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(xxv) "provost-marshal" means a person appointed as such under section 108 and includes any of`
  line `his deputies or assistants or any other person legally exercising authority under him or on his behalf;`
  line
  line `(xxvi) "regulation" includes a regulation made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(xxvii) "superior officer", when used in relation to a person subject to this Act, includes a warrant`
  line `officer and a non-commissioned officer, and as regards persons serving under such conditions as may be`
  line `prescribed, an officer, junior commissioned officer, warrant officer, petty officer and non-commissioned`
  line `officer of the regular Army or the Navy;`
  line
  line `(xxviii) "unit" includes--`
  line
  line `(a) anybody of officers and airmen for which a separate authorised establishment exists;`
  line
  line `(b) any separate body of persons subject to this Act employed on any service and not attached`
  line `to a unit as aforesaid;`
  line
  line `(c) any other separate body of persons composed wholly or partly of persons subject to this`
  line `Act, and specified as a unit by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(xxix) "warrant officer" means a person appointed, gazetted or in pay as a warrant officer of the`
  line `Air Force and includes an acting warrant officer, a master warrant officer, and a warrant officer`
  line `of ^5[any Air Force Reserve or the Auxiliary Air Force] who is for the time being subject to this Act;`
  line
  line `(xxx)`
  line `^6[all words (except the word "India")] and expressions used herein and defined in the Indian`
  line `Penal Code (45 of 1860) and not hereinbefore defined shall be deemed to have the meanings`
  line `respectively assigned to them by that Code.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs by Act 62 of 1952, s. 35, for "the Indian Air Force Volunteer Reserve" (w.e.f. 15-8-1955).`
  line
  line `2. Subs by Act 19 of 1955, s. 2 and the Schedule, for "Commander-in-Chief" (w.e.f. 15-8-1955).`
  line
  line `3. Subs by s. 2 and the Schedule, ibid., for clause (xiv) (w.e.f. 15-8-1955).`
  line
  line `4. The words other "than the State of Jammu and Kashmir" omitted by Act 13 of 1975, s. 2 (w.e.f. 25-1-1975).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 62 of 1952, s. 35, for "Indian Air Force Volunteer Reserve" (w.e.f. 15-8-1955).`
  line
  line `6. Subs by Act 13 of 1975, s. 2, for "all words" (w.e.f. 25-1-1975).`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (3134)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Application of Act to certain forces under the Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=3134&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central`
  line `Government may, by notification, apply with or without modifications, all or any of the provisions of this`
  line `Act to any force raised and maintained in India and suspend the operation of any other enactment for the`
  line `time being applicable to the said force.`
  line
  line `(2) The provisions of this Act so applied shall have effect in respect of persons belonging to the said`
  line `force as they have effect in respect of persons subject to this Act holding in the Air Force the same or`
  line `equivalent rank as the aforesaid persons hold for the time being in the said force.`
  line
  line `(3) The provisions of this Act so applied shall also have effect in respect of persons who are`
  line `employed by, or are in the service of, or are followers of, or accompany any portion of the said force as`
  line `they have effect in respect of persons subject to this Act under clause (d) of section 2.`
  line
  line `(4) While any of the provisions of this Act apply to the said force, the Central Government may, by`
  line `notification, direct by what authority any jurisdiction, powers or duties incident to the operation of these`
  line `provisions shall be exercised or performed in respect of the said force.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (3135)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Special provision as to rank in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=3135&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification,`
  line `direct that any person or class of persons subject to this Act under clause (d) of section 2, shall be so`
  line `subject as officers, warrant officers or non-commissioned officers, and may authorise any officer to give a`
  line `like direction and to cancel such direction.`
  line
  line `(2) All persons subject to this Act other than officers, warrant officers and non-commissioned officers`
  line `shall, if they are not persons in respect of whom a notification or direction under sub-section (1) is in`
  line `force, be deemed to be of rank inferior to that of a non-commissioned officer.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (3136)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Commanding Officer of person subject to Air Force law under clause (d) of section 2.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=3136&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1)`
  line `Every person subject to this Act, under clause (d) of section 2, shall, for the purposes of this Act, be`
  line `deemed to be under the commanding officer of the unit, or detachment, if any, to which he is attached,`
  line `and if he is not so attached under the command of any officer who may for the time being be named as his`
  line `commanding officer by the officer commanding the force with which such person may for the time being`
  line `be serving, or of any other prescribed officer, or, if no such officer is named or prescribed, under the`
  line `command of the said officer commanding the force.`
  line
  line `(2) An officer commanding a force shall not place a person subject to this Act under clause (d) of`
  line `section 2 under the command of an officer of official rank inferior to that of such person if there is present`
  line `at the place where such person is any officer of higher rank under whose command he can be placed.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (3137)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Officers exercising powers in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=3137&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whenever persons subject to this Act are serving`
  line `under an officer commanding any air force formation not in this section specifically named, and being, in`
  line `the opinion of the Central Government, not less than a squadron, the said Government may prescribe the`
  line `officer by whom the powers which, under this Act, may be exercised by air officers in charge of`
  line `commands, and officers commanding groups, wings and squadrons shall, as regards such persons, be`
  line exercised.
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may confer such powers either absolutely, or subject to such restrictions,`
  line `reservations, exceptions and conditions as it may think fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (3138)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Power to declare persons to be on active service.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=3138&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in`
  line `clause (i) of section 4, the Central Government may, by notification, declare that any person or class of`
  line `persons subject to this Act shall, with reference to any area in which they may be serving or with`
  line `reference to any provision of this Act or of any other law for the time being in force, be deemed to be on`
  line `active service within the meaning of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (3139)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Commission and appointment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=3139&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `The President may grant, to such person as he thinks fit a`
  line `commission as an officer or appoint any person as a warrant officer of the Air Force.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (3140)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Ineligibility of aliens for enrolment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=3140&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `No person who is not a citizen of India shall, except with`
  line `the consent of the Central Government signified in writing, be enrolled in the Air Force:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this section shall bar the enrolment of the subjects of Nepal in the`
  line `Air Force.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (3141)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Ineligibility of females for enrolment or employment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=3141&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `No female shall be eligible for`
  line `enrolment or employment in the Air Force, except in such corps, department, branch or other body`
  line `forming part of, or attached to any portion of, the Air Force as the Central Government may, by`
  line `notification, specify in this behalf:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this section shall affect the provisions of any law for the time`
  line `being in force providing for the raising and maintenance of any service auxiliary to the Air Force or any`
  line `branch thereof in which females are eligible for enrolment or employment.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (3142)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Procedure before enrolling officer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=3142&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `Upon the appearance before the prescribed enrolling`
  line `officer of any person desirous of being enrolled, the enrolling officer shall read and explain to him, or`
  line `cause to be read and explained to him, in his presence, the conditions of the service for which he is to be`
  line `enrolled; and shall put to him the questions set forth in the prescribed form of enrolment, and shall, after`
  line `having cautioned him that if he makes a false answer to any such question he will be liable to punishment`
  line `under this Act, record or cause to be recorded his answer to each such question.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (3143)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Mode of enrolment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=3143&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `If, after complying with the provisions of section 13, the enrolling officer`
  line `is satisfied that the person desirous of being enrolled fully understands the questions put to him and`
  line `consents to the conditions of service, and if such officer perceives no impediment, he shall sign and shall`
  line `also cause such person to sign the enrolment paper, and such person shall thereupon be deemed to be`
  line enrolled.
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (3144)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Validity of enrolment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=3144&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `Every person who has for the space of three months been in receipt of`
  line `pay as a person enrolled under this Act and been borne on the rolls of any unit shall be deemed to have`
  line `been duly enrolled, and shall not be entitled to claim his discharge on the ground of any irregularity or`
  line `illegality in his enrolment or on any other ground whatsoever; and if any person, in receipt of such pay`
  line `and borne on the rolls as aforesaid, claims his discharge before the expiry of three months from his`
  line `enrolment, no such irregularity or illegality or other ground shall, until he is discharged in pursuance of`
  line `his claim, affect his position as an enrolled person under this Act or invalidate any proceedings, act or`
  line `thing taken or done prior to his discharge.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (3145)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Persons to be attested.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=3145&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `The following persons shall be attested, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) all persons enrolled as combatants;`
  line
  line `(b) all persons selected to hold a non-commissioned or acting non-commissioned rank; and`
  line
  line `(c) all other persons subject to this Act as may be prescribed by the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (3146)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Mode of attestation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=3146&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) When a person who is to be attested is reported fit for duty, or has`
  line `completed the prescribed period of probation, an oath or affirmation shall be administered to him in the`
  line `prescribed form by his commanding officer in front of his unit or such portion thereof as may be present,`
  line `or by any other prescribed persons.`
  line
  line `(2) The form of oath or affirmation prescribed under this section shall contain a promise that the`
  line `person to be attested will bear true allegiance to the Constitution of India as by law established, and that`
  line `he will serve in the Air Force and go wherever he is ordered by land, sea or air, and that he will obey all`
  line `commands of any officer set over him, even to the peril of his life.`
  line
  line `(3) The fact of an enrolled person having taken the oath or affirmation directed by this section to be`
  line `taken shall be entered on his enrolment paper and authenticated by the signature of the officer`
  line `administering the oath or affirmation.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (3147)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Tenure of service under the Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=3147&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `Every person subject to this Act shall hold office during the`
  line `pleasure of the President.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (3148)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Termination of service by Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=3148&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of this Act and the`
  line `rules and regulations made thereunder, the Central Government may dismiss, or remove from the service`
  line `any person subject to this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (3149)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Dismissal, removal or reduction by Chief of the Air staff and other officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 19 of 1955, s. 2 and the Schedule, for "the Commander-in-Chief"(w.e.f. 7-5-1955).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=3149&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1)`
  line `^1[The Chief`
  line `of the Air Staff] may dismiss or remove from the service any person subject to this Act other than an`
  line officer.
  line
  line `(2)`
  line `^1[The Chief of the Air Staff] may reduce to a lower grade or rank or the ranks, any warrant officer`
  line `or any non-commissioned officer.`
  line
  line `(3) An officer having power not less than an air officer in charge of a command or equivalent`
  line `commander or any prescribed officer may dismiss or remove from the service any person serving under`
  line `his command other than an officer or a warrant officer.`
  line
  line `(4) On active service, an officer commanding the air forces in the field may reduce to a lower rank or`
  line `to the ranks any warrant officer or non-commissioned officer under his command.`
  line
  line `(5)`
  line `^1[The Chief of the Air Staff] or an officer specified in sub-section (3) may reduce to a lower class`
  line `in the ranks any airman other than a warrant officer or non-commissioned officer.`
  line
  line `(6) The commanding officer of an acting non-commissioned officer may order him to revert to his`
  line `substantive rank as a non-commissioned officer, or if he had no such substantive rank, to the ranks.`
  line
  line `(7) The exercise of any powers under this section shall be subject to the other provisions contained in`
  line `this Act and the rules and regulations made thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (3150)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Power to modify certain fundamental rights in their application to persons subject to this Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=3150&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of any law for the time being in force relating to the Air Force or to any`
  line `branch thereof, the Central Government may, by notification, make rules a restricting in such manner and`
  line `to such extent as may be specified the right of any person subject to this Act--`
  line
  line `(a) to be a member of, or to be associated in any way with, any trade union or labour union, or`
  line `any class of trade or labour unions or any society, institution or association, or any class of societies,`
  line `institutions or associations;`
  line
  line `(b) to attend or address any meeting or to take part in any demonstration organised by any body`
  line `of persons for any political or other purposes;`
  line
  line `(c) to communicate with the press or to publish or cause to be published any book, letter or other`
  line document.
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (3151)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Retirement, release or discharge.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=3151&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `Any person subject to this Act may be retired, released or`
  line `discharged from the service by such authority and in such manner as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (3152)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Certificate on termination of service.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=3152&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `Every warrant officer, or enrolled person who is`
  line `dismissed, removed, discharged, retired or released from the service shall be furnished by his`
  line `commanding officer with a certificate, in the language which is the mother tongue of such person and also`
  line `in the English language setting forth--`
  line
  line `(a) the authority terminating his service;`
  line
  line `(b) the cause for such termination; and`
  line
  line `(c) the full period of his service in the Air Force.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (3153)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Discharge or dismissal when out of India.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=3153&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person enrolled under this Act who is`
  line `entitled under the conditions of his enrolment to be discharged, or whose discharge is ordered by`
  line `competent authority, and who, when he is so entitled or ordered to be discharged, is serving out of India,`
  line `and requests to be sent to India, shall, before being discharged, be sent to India with all convenient speed.`
  line
  line `(2) Any person enrolled under this Act who is dismissed from the service and who, when he is so`
  line `dismissed, is serving out of India, shall be sent to India with all convenient speed.`
  line
  line `(3) Where any such person as is mentioned in sub-section (2) is sentenced to dismissal combined with`
  line `any other punishment, such other punishment or, in the case of a sentence of transportation, imprisonment`
  line `or detention, a portion of such sentence may be inflicted before he is sent to India.`
  line
  line `(4) for the purposes of this section, the word, "discharge" shall include release, and the word`
  line `dismissal shall include removal.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (3154)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Authorised deductions only to be made from pay.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=3154&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `The pay of every person subject to this Act`
  line `due to him as such under any regulation, for the time being in force, shall be paid without any deduction`
  line `other than the deductions authorised by or under this or any other Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (3155)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Remedy of aggrieved airmen.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by act 19 of 1955, s. 2 and the Schedule, for "the Commander-in-Chief" (w.e.f. 7-5-1955).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=3155&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any airman who deems himself wronged by any superior or`
  line `other officer may, if not attached to a unit or detachment, complain to the officer under whose command`
  line `or orders he is serving; and may, if attached to a unit or detachment, complain to the officer commanding`
  line `the same.`
  line
  line `(2) When the ofbrficer complained against is the officer to whom any complaint should, under subsection`
  line `(1), be preferred, the aggrieved airman may complain to such officer's next superior officer, and if`
  line `he thinks himself wronged by such superior officer, he may complain to ^1[the Chief of the Air Staff.]`
  line
  line `(3) Every officer receiving any such complaint shall make as complete an investigation into it as may`
  line `be possible for giving full redress to the complainant; or, when necessary, refer the complaint to superior`
  line authority.
  line
  line `(4) Every such complaint shall be preferred in such manner as may from time to time be specified by`
  line `the proper authority.`
  line
  line `(5) The Central Government may revise any decision by a ^1[the Chief of the Air staff] under`
  line `sub section (2), but subject thereto, the decision of ^1[the Chief of the Air Staff] shall be final.`
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (3156)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Remedy of aggrieved officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=3156&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `Any officer who deems himself wronged by his commanding`
  line `officer or any superior officer and who on due application made to his commanding officer does not`
  line `receive the redress to which he considers himself entitled, may complain to the Central Government in`
  line `such manner as may from time to time be specified by the proper authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (3157)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Immunity from attachment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=3157&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `The arms, clothes, equipment, accoutrements or necessaries of`
  line `any person subject to this Act shall not be seized, and the pay and allowances of any such person or any`
  line `part thereof shall not be attached, by direction of any civil or revenue court or any revenue officer, in`
  line `satisfaction of any decree or order enforceable against him.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (3158)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Immunity from arrest for debt.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=3158&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `(1) No person subject to this Act shall, so long as he belongs`
  line `to the Forces be liable to be arrested for debt under any process issued by, or by the authority of, any civil`
  line `or revenue court or revenue officer.`
  line
  line `(2) The judge of any such court or the said officer may examine into any complaint made by such`
  line `person or his superior officer of the arrest of such person contrary to the provisions of this section, and`
  line `may, by warrant under his hand, discharge the person, and award reasonable costs to the complainant,`
  line `who may recover those costs in like manner as he might have recovered costs awarded to him by a decree`
  line `against the person obtaining the process.`
  line
  line `(3) For the recovery of such costs no court-fee shall be payable by the complainant.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (3159)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Immunity of persons attending courts-martial from arrest.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=3159&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `(1) No presiding officer or`
  line `member of a court-martial, no judge advocate, no party to any proceeding before a court-martial, or his`
  line `legal practitioner or agent, and no witness acting in obedience to a summons to attend a court-martial`
  line `shall, while proceeding to, attending, or returning from, a court-martial, be liable to arrest under civil or`
  line `revenue process.`
  line
  line `(2) If any such person is arrested under any such process, he may be discharged by order of the`
  line court-martial.
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (3160)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `Privileges of reservists.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by the Act 62 of 1952, s. 35, for "the Air Force Reserve" (w.e.f. 15-8-1955).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=3160&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `Every person belonging to ^1[any Air Force Reserve or the Auxiliary`
  line `Air Force] shall, when called out for, or engaged in, or returning from, training or service, be entitled to`
  line `all the privileges accorded by sections 28 and 29 to a person subject to this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (3161)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 32
  title `Priority in respect of Air Force personnel's litigation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=3161&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `(1) On the presentation to any court`
  line `by or on behalf of any person subject to this Act of a certificate, from the proper air force authority, of`
  line `leave of absence having been granted to or applied for by him for the purpose of prosecuting or defending`
  line `any suit or other proceeding in such court, the court shall, on the application of such person, arrange, so`
  line `far as may be possible, for the hearing and final disposal of such suit or other proceeding within the`
  line `period of the leave so granted or applied for.`
  line
  line `(2) The certificate from the proper air force authority shall state the first and last day of the leave or`
  line `intended leave, and set forth a description of the case with respect to which the leave was granted or`
  line `applied for.`
  line
  line `(3) No fee shall be payable to the court in respect of the presentation of any such certificate, or of any`
  line `application by or on behalf of any such person, for priority for the hearing of his case.`
  line
  line `(4) Where the court is unable to arrange for the hearing and final disposal of the suit or other`
  line `proceeding within the period of such leave or intended leave as aforesaid, it shall record its reasons for its`
  line `inability to do so, and shall cause a copy thereof to be furnished to such person on his application without`
  line `any payment whatever by him in respect either of the application for such copy or of the copy itself.`
  line
  line `(5) If in any case a question arises as to the proper air force authority qualified to grant such`
  line `certificate as aforesaid. Such question shall be at once referred by the court to an officer having power not`
  line `less than a group commander or equivalent commander whose decision shall be final.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (3162)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 33
  title `Saving of rights and privileges under other laws.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=3162&sectionno=33&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `The rights and privileges specified in the`
  line `preceding sections of this Chapter shall be in addition to any others conferred on persons subject to this`
  line `Act or on members of the regular Army, Navy and Air Force generally by any other law for the time`
  line `being in force.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (3163)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 34
  title `Offences in relation to the enemy and punishable with death.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=3163&sectionno=34&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `Any person subject to this Act`
  line `who commits any of the following offences, that is to say,--`
  line
  line `(a) shamefully abandons or delivers up any garrison, fortress, post, place or guard, committed to`
  line `his charge, or which it is his duty to defend, or uses any means to compel or induce any commanding`
  line `officer or other person to commit the said act; or`
  line
  line `(b) intentionally uses any means to compel or induce any person subject to military, naval or air`
  line `force law to abstain from acting against the enemy, or to discourage such person from acting against`
  line `the enemy; or`
  line
  line `(c) in the presence of the enemy, shamefully casts away his arms, ammunition, tools or`
  line `equipment or misbehaves in such manner as to show cowardice; or`
  line
  line `(d) treacherously holds correspondence with, or communicates intelligence to, the enemy or any`
  line `person in arms against the Union; or`
  line
  line `(e) directly or indirectly assists the enemy with money, arms, ammunition, stores or supplies; or`
  line
  line `(f) treacherously or through cowardice sends a flag of truce to the enemy; or`
  line
  line `(g) in time of war or during any air force operation, intentionally occasions a false alarm in`
  line `action, camp or quarters or spreads reports calculated to create alarm or despondency; or`
  line
  line `(h) in time of action leaves his commanding officer or his post, guard, piquet, patrol or party`
  line `without being regularly relieved or without leave; or`
  line
  line `(i) having been made a prisoner of war, voluntarily serves with or aids the enemy; or`
  line
  line `(j) knowingly harbours or protects an enemy not being a prisoner; or`
  line
  line `(k) being a sentry in time of war or alarm, sleeps upon his post or is intoxicated; or`
  line
  line `(l) knowingly does any act calculated to imperil the success of the military, naval or air forces of`
  line `India or any forces co-operating therewith or any part of such forces; or`
  line
  line `(m) treacherously or shamefully causes the capture or destruction by the enemy of any aircraft`
  line `belonging to the forces; or`
  line
  line `(n) treacherously uses any false air signal or alters or interferes with any air signal; or`
  line
  line `(o) when ordered by his superior officer or otherwise under orders to carry out any air force`
  line `operations, treacherously or shamefully fails to use his utmost exertions to carry such orders into`
  line effect,
  line
  line `shall, on conviction by court-martial, be liable to suffer death or such less punishment as is in this Act`
  line mentioned.
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (3164)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 35
  title `Offences in relation to the enemy and not punishable with death.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=3164&sectionno=35&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `Any person subject to this`
  line `Act who commits any of the following offences, that is to say,--`
  line
  line `(a) is taken prisoner, by want of due precaution, or through disobedience of orders, or wilful`
  line `neglect of duty, or having been taken prisoner, fails to rejoin his service when able to do so; or`
  line
  line `(b) without due authority holds correspondence with or communicates intelligence to the enemy;`
  line `or having come by the knowledge of any such correspondence or communication wilfully omits to`
  line `discover it immediately to his commanding or other superior officer; or`
  line
  line `(c) without due authority sends a flag of truce to the enemy; or`
  line
  line `(d) negligently causes the capture or destruction by the enemy of any aircraft belonging to the`
  line `Government; or.`
  line
  line `(e) when ordered by his superior officer, or otherwise under orders to carry out any warlike`
  line `operations in the air, negligently or through other default fails to use his utmost exertions to carry`
  line `such orders into effect;`
  line
  line `shall, on conviction by court-martial, be liable to suffer imprisonment for a term which may extend to`
  line `fourteen years or such less punishment as is in this Act mentioned.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (3165)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 36
  title `Offences punishable more severely on active service than at other times.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=3165&sectionno=36&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `Any person subject`
  line `to this Act who commits any of the following offences, that is to say,--`
  line
  line `(a) forces a safeguard, or forces or uses criminal force to a sentry; or`
  line
  line `(b) breaks into any house or other place in search of plunder; or`
  line
  line `(c) being a sentry sleeps upon his post, or is intoxicated; or`
  line
  line `(d) without orders from his superior officer leaves his guard, piquet, patrol or post; or`
  line
  line `(e) intentionally or through neglect occasions a false alarm in camp or quarters; or spreads reports`
  line `calculated to create unnecessary alarm or despondency; or`
  line
  line `(f) makes known the parole, watchword or countersign to any person not entitled to receive it; or`
  line `knowingly gives a parole, watchword or countersign different from what he received; or`
  line
  line `(g) without due authority alters or interferes with any air signal;`
  line
  line `shall, on conviction by court-martial,`
  line
  line `if he commits any such offence when on active service, be liable to suffer imprisonment for a`
  line `term which may extend to fourteen years or such less punishment as is in this Act mentioned; and`
  line
  line `if he commits any such offence when not on active service, be liable to suffer imprisonment for a`
  line `term which may extend to seven years or such less punishment as is in this Act mentioned.`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (3166)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 37
  title Mutiny.
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=3166&sectionno=37&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `Any person subject to this Act who commits any of the following offences, that is to`
  line say,--
  line
  line `(a) begins, incites, causes, or conspires, with any other persons to cause, any mutiny in the military,`
  line `naval or air forces of India or any forces co-operating therewith; or`
  line
  line `(b) joins in any such mutiny; or`
  line
  line `(c) being present at any such mutiny, does not use his utmost endeavours to suppress the same; or`
  line
  line `(d) knowing or having reason to believe in the existence of any such mutiny, or of any intention to`
  line `commit such mutiny or any such conspiracy, does not, without delay, give information thereof to his`
  line `commanding or other superior officer; or`
  line
  line `(e) endeavours to seduce any person in the military, naval or air forces of India from his duty or`
  line `allegiance to the Union,`
  line
  line `shall, on conviction by court-martial, be liable to suffer death or such less punishment as is in this Act`
  line mentioned.
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (3167)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 38
  title `Desertion and aiding desertion.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=3167&sectionno=38&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person subject to this Act who deserts or attempts to`
  line `desert the service shall on conviction by court-martial,`
  line
  line `if he commits the offence on active service or when under orders for active service, be liable to`
  line `suffer death or such less punishment as is in this Act mentioned; and`
  line
  line `if he commits the offence under any other circumstances, be liable to suffer imprisonment for a`
  line `term which may extend to seven years or such less punishment as is in this Act mentioned.`
  line
  line `(2) Any person subject to this Act who knowingly harbours any such deserter shall, on conviction by`
  line `court-martial, be liable to suffer imprisonment for a term which may extend to seven years or such less`
  line `punishment as is in this Act mentioned.`
  line
  line `(3) Any person subject to this Act who, being cognizant of any desertion or attempt at desertion of a`
  line `person subject to this Act, does not forthwith give notice to his own or some other superior officer, or take`
  line `any steps in his power to cause such person to be apprehended, shall, on conviction by court-martial, be`
  line `liable to suffer imprisonment for a term which may extend to two years or such less punishment as is in`
  line `this Act mentioned.`
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (3168)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 39
  title `Absence without leave.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=3168&sectionno=39&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `Any person subject to this Act who commits any of the following`
  line `offences, that is to say,--`
  line
  line `(a) absents himself without leave; or`
  line
  line `(b) without sufficient cause overstays leave granted to him; or`
  line
  line `(c) being on leave of absence and having received information from proper authority that any unit`
  line `or detachment to which he belongs, has been ordered on active service, fails, without sufficient cause,`
  line `to re-join without delay; or`
  line
  line `(d) without sufficient cause fails to appear at the time fixed, at the parade or place appointed for`
  line `exercise or duty; or`
  line
  line `(e) when on parade, or on the line of march, without sufficient cause or without leave from his`
  line `superior officer, quits the parade or line of march; or`
  line
  line `(f) when in camp or elsewhere, is found beyond any limits fixed, or in any place prohibited, by`
  line `any general, local or other order, without a pass or written leave from his superior officer; or`
  line
  line `(g) without leave from his superior officer or without due cause, absents himself from any school`
  line `when duly ordered to attend there,`
  line
  line `shall, on conviction by court-martial, be liable to suffer imprisonment for a term which may extend to`
  line `three years or such less punishment as is in this Act mentioned.`
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (3169)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 40
  title `Striking or threatening superior officer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=3169&sectionno=40&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `Any person subject to this Act who commits any of`
  line `the following offences, that is to say,--`
  line
  line `(a) uses criminal force to, or assaults his superior officer; or`
  line
  line `(b) uses threatening language to such officer; or`
  line
  line `(c) uses insubordinate language to such officer,`
  line
  line `shall, or, conviction by court-martial,`
  line
  line `if such officer is at the time in the execution of his office or, if the offence is committed on active`
  line `service, be liable to suffer imprisonment for a term which may extend to fourteen years or such less`
  line `punishment as is in this Act mentioned; and`
  line
  line `in other cases, be liable to suffer imprisonment for a term which may extend to ten years or such`
  line `less punishment as is in this Act mentioned:`
  line
  line `Provided that in the case of an offence specified in clause (c), the imprisonment shall not exceed five`
  line years.
obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (3170)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 41
  title `Disobedience to superior officer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=3170&sectionno=41&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person subject to this Act who disobeys in such`
  line `manner as to show a wilful defiance of authority any lawful command given personally by his superior`
  line `officer in the execution of his office whether the same is given orally or in writing or by signal or`
  line `otherwise shall, on conviction by court-martial, be liable to suffer imprisonment for a term which may`
  line `extend to fourteen years or such less punishment as is in this Act mentioned.`
  line
  line `(2) Any person subject to this Act who disobeys any lawful command given by his superior officer`
  line `shall, on conviction by court-martial,`
  line
  line `if he commits such offence when on active service, be liable to suffer imprisonment for a term`
  line `which may extend to five years or such less punishment as is in this Act mentioned; and`
  line
  line `if he commits such offence when not on active service, be liable to suffer imprisonment for a`
  line `term which may extend to fourteen years or such less punishment as is in this Act mentioned.`
obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (3171)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 42
  title `Insubordination and obstruction.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=3171&sectionno=42&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `Any person subject to this Act who commits any of the`
  line `following offences, that is to say,--`
  line
  line `(a) being concerned in any quarrel, affray or disorder, refuses to obey any officer, though of`
  line `inferior rank, who orders him into arrest, or uses criminal force to or assaults any such officer; or`
  line
  line `(b) uses criminal force to, or assaults any person, whether subject to this Act or not, in whose`
  line `custody he is lawfully placed, and whether he is or is not this superior officer; or`
  line
  line `(c) resists an escort whose duty it is to apprehend him or to have him in charge; or`
  line
  line `(d) breaks out of barracks, camp or quarters; or`
  line
  line `(e) neglects to obey any general, local or other order; or`
  line
  line `(f) impedes the provost-marshal or any person lawfully acting on his behalf or, when called upon,`
  line `refuses to assist in the execution of his duty a provost-marshal or any person lawfully acting on his`
  line `behalf; or`
  line
  line `(g) uses criminal force to or assaults any person bringing provisions or supplies to the Forces,`
  line
  line `shall, on conviction by court-martial, be liable to suffer imprisonment for a term which may extend, in the`
  line `case of the offences specified in clauses(d) and (e) to two years, and in the case of the offences specified`
  line `in the other clauses to ten years or such less punishment as is in this Act mentioned.`
obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (3172)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 43
  title `Fraudulent enrolment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=3172&sectionno=43&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line `Any person subject to this Act who commits any of the following`
  line `offences, that is to say,--`
  line
  line `(a) without having obtained a regular discharge from the Air Force or otherwise fulfilled the`
  line `conditions enabling him to enroll or enter, enrolls himself in, or enters the said force or any part of the`
  line `military or the naval forces of India; or`
  line
  line `(b) is concerned in the enrolment in any part of the Forces, of any person when he knows or has`
  line `reason to believe such person to be so circumstanced that by enrolling he commits an offence against`
  line `this Act,`
  line
  line `shall, on conviction by court-martial, be liable to suffer imprisonment for a term which may extend to five`
  line `years or such less punishment as is in this Act mentioned.`
obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (3173)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 44
  title `False answers on enrolment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=3173&sectionno=44&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `Any person having become subject to this Act who is discovered`
  line `to have made at the time of enrolment a wilfully false answer to any question set forth in the prescribed`
  line `form of enrolment which has been put to him by the enrolling officer before whom he appears for the`
  line `purpose of being enrolled, shall, on conviction by court-martial, be liable to suffer imprisonment for a`
  line `term which may extend to five years or such less punishment as is in this Act mentioned.`
obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (3174)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 45
  title `Unbecoming conduct`
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=3174&sectionno=45&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line `Any officer or warrant officer who behaves in a manner unbecoming his`
  line `position and the character expected of him shall, on conviction by court-martial, if he is an officer, be`
  line `liable to be cashiered or to suffer such less punishment as is in this Act mentioned; and if he is a warrant`
  line `officer, be liable to be dismissed or to suffer such less punishment as is in this Act mentioned.`
obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_46:
  sectionId (21678)
  sectionNo (46)
  orderNo 46
  title `Certain forms of disgraceful conduct.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_46_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=21678&sectionno=46&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_46_content:
  string
  line `Any person subject to this Act who commits any of the`
  line `following offences, that is to say,--`
  line
  line `(a) is guilty of any disgraceful conduct of a cruel, indecent or unnatural kind; or`
  line
  line `(b) malingers, or feigns, or produces disease or infirmity in himself, or intentionally delays his`
  line `cure or aggravates his disease or infirmity; or`
  line
  line `(c) with intent to render himself or any other person unfit for service, voluntarily causes hurt to`
  line `himself or that person,`
  line
  line `shall, on conviction by court-martial, be liable to suffer imprisonment for a term which may extend to`
  line `seven years or such less punishment as is in this Act mentioned.`
obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_47:
  sectionId (21679)
  sectionNo (47)
  orderNo 47
  title `III-treating a subordinate`
  content obj_root_law_sections_47_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=21679&sectionno=47&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_47_content:
  string
  line `Any officer, warrant officer or non-commissioned officer, who uses`
  line `criminal force to or otherwise ill-treats any person subject to this Act, being his subordinate in rank or`
  line `position, shall, on conviction by court-martial, be liable to suffer imprisonment for a term which may`
  line `extend to seven years or such less punishment as is in this Act mentioned.`
obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_48:
  sectionId (21680)
  sectionNo (48)
  orderNo 48
  title Intoxication.
  content obj_root_law_sections_48_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=21680&sectionno=48&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_48_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person subject to this Act who is found in a state of intoxication, whether`
  line `on duty or not, shall, on conviction by court-martial, if he is an officer, be liable to be cashiered or to`
  line `suffer such less punishment as is in this Act mentioned; and if he is not an officer, be liable, subject to the`
  line `provisions of sub-section (2), to suffer imprisonment for a term which may extend to two years or such`
  line `less punishment as is in this Act mentioned.`
  line
  line `(2) Where an offence of being intoxicated is committed by a person other than an officer when not on`
  line `active service or not on duty, the period of imprisonment awarded shall not exceed six months.`
obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_49:
  sectionId (21681)
  sectionNo (49)
  orderNo 49
  title `Permitting escape of person in custody.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_49_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=21681&sectionno=49&orderno=49&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_49_content:
  string
  line `Any person subject to this Act who commits any of`
  line `the following offences, that is to say,--`
  line
  line `(a) when in command of a guard, piquet, patrol or post, releases without proper authority,`
  line `whether wilfully or without reasonable excuse, any person committed to his charge or refuses to`
  line `receive any prisoner or person so committed ; or`
  line
  line `(b) wilfully or without reasonable excuse allows to escape any person who is committed to his`
  line `charge or whom it is his duty to keep on guard;`
  line
  line `shall, on conviction by court-martial, be liable, if he has acted, willfully, to suffer imprisonment for a`
  line `term which may extend to fourteen years or such less punishment as is in this Act mentioned; and if he`
  line `has not acted willfully, to suffer imprisonment for a term which may extend to two years or such less`
  line `punishment as is in this Act mentioned.`
obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_50:
  sectionId (21682)
  sectionNo (50)
  orderNo 50
  title `Irregularity in connection with arrest or confinement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_50_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=21682&sectionno=50&orderno=50&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_50_content:
  string
  line `Any person subject to this Act who`
  line `commits any of the following offences, that is to say,--`
  line
  line `(a) unnecessarily detains a person in arrest or confinement without bringing him to trial, or fails`
  line `to bring his case before the proper authority for investigation; or`
  line
  line `(b) having committed a person to air force custody fails without reasonable cause to deliver at the`
  line `time of such committal, or as soon as practicable, and in any case within forty-eight hours thereafter,`
  line `to the officer or other person into whose custody the person arrested is committed, an account in`
  line `writing signed by himself of the offence with which the person so committed is charged;`
  line
  line `shall, on conviction by court-martial, be liable to suffer imprisonment for a term which may extend to two`
  line `years or such less punishment as is in this Act mentioned.`
obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_51:
  sectionId (21683)
  sectionNo (51)
  orderNo 51
  title `Escape from custody.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_51_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=21683&sectionno=51&orderno=51&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_51_content:
  string
  line `Any person subject to this Act who, being in lawful custody, escapes or`
  line `attempts to escape, shall, on conviction by court-martial, be liable to suffer imprisonment for a term`
  line `which may extend to five years or such less punishment as is in this Act mentioned.`
obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_52:
  sectionId (21684)
  sectionNo (52)
  orderNo 52
  title `Offences to respect of property.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_52_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=21684&sectionno=52&orderno=52&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_52_content:
  string
  line `Any person subject to this Act who commits any of the`
  line `following offences, that is to say,--`
  line
  line `(a) commits theft of any property belonging to the Government, or to any military, naval or air`
  line `force mess, band or institution, or to any person subject to military, naval or air force law; or`
  line
  line `(b) dishonestly misappropriates or converts to his own use any such property; or`
  line
  line `(c) commits criminal breach of trust in respect of any such property; or`
  line
  line `(d) dishonestly receives or retains any such property in respect of which any of the offences under`
  line `clauses (a), (b) and (c) has been committed, knowing or having reason to believe the commission of`
  line `such offence; or`
  line
  line `(e) wilfully destroys or injures any property of the Government entrusted to him; or`
  line
  line `(f) does any other thing with intent to defraud, or to cause wrongful gain to one person or`
  line `wrongful loss to another person;`
  line
  line `shall, on conviction by court-martial, be liable to suffer imprisonment for a term which may extend to ten`
  line `years or such less punishment as is in this Act mentioned.`
obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_53:
  sectionId (21685)
  sectionNo (53)
  orderNo 53
  title `Extortion and corruption.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_53_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=21685&sectionno=53&orderno=53&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_53_content:
  string
  line `Any person subject to this Act who commits any of the following`
  line `offences, that is to say,--`
  line
  line `(a) commits extortion; or`
  line
  line `(b) without proper authority extracts from any person money, provisions or services;`
  line
  line `shall, on conviction by court-martial, be liable to suffer imprisonment for a term which may extend to ten`
  line `years or such less punishment as is in this Act mentioned.`
obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_54:
  sectionId (21686)
  sectionNo (54)
  orderNo 54
  title `Making away with equipment`
  content obj_root_law_sections_54_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=21686&sectionno=54&orderno=54&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_54_content:
  string
  line `Any person subject to this Act who commits any of the`
  line `following offences, that is to say,--`
  line
  line `(a) makes away with, or is concerned in making away with, any arms, ammunition, equipment,`
  line `instruments, tools, clothing or any other thing being the property of the Government issued to him for`
  line `his use or entrusted to him; or`
  line
  line `(b) loses by neglect anything mentioned in clause (a); or`
  line
  line `(c) sells, pawns, destroys or defaces any medal or decoration granted to him;`
  line
  line `shall, on conviction by court-martial, be liable to suffer imprisonment for a term which may extend, in the`
  line `case of the offences specified in clause (a) to ten years, and in the case of the offences specified in the`
  line `other clauses to five years, or such less punishment as is in this Act mentioned.`
obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_55:
  sectionId (21687)
  sectionNo (55)
  orderNo 55
  title `Injury to property.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_55_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=21687&sectionno=55&orderno=55&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_55_content:
  string
  line `Any person subject to this Act who commits any of the following offences,`
  line `that is to say,--`
  line
  line `(a) destroys or injures any property mentioned in clause (a) of section 54, or any property`
  line `belonging to any military, naval or air force mess, band or institution, or to any person subject to`
  line `military, naval or air force law, or serving with, or attached to the Air Force, or;`
  line
  line `(b) commits any act which causes damage to, or destruction of, any property of the Government`
  line `by fire; or`
  line
  line `(c) kills, injures, makes away with, ill-treats or loses any animal entrusted to him;`
  line
  line `shall, on conviction by court-martial, be liable, if he has acted willfully, to suffer imprisonment for a term`
  line `which may extend to fourteen years or such less punishment as is in this Act mentioned; and if he has`
  line `acted without reasonable excuse to suffer imprisonment for a term which may extend to seven years or`
  line `such less punishment as is in this Act mentioned.`
obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_56:
  sectionId (21688)
  sectionNo (56)
  orderNo 56
  title `False accusation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_56_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=21688&sectionno=56&orderno=56&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_56_content:
  string
  line `Any person subject to this Act who commits any of the following offences,`
  line `that is to say,--`
  line
  line `(a) makes a false accusation against any person subject to this Act, knowing or having reason to`
  line `believe such accusation to be false; or`
  line
  line `(b) in making a complaint under section 26 or section 27 makes any statement affecting the`
  line `character of any person subject to this Act, knowing or having reason to believe such statement to be`
  line `false, or knowingly and wilfully suppresses any material facts;`
  line
  line `shall, on conviction by court-martial, be liable to suffer imprisonment for a term which may extend to five`
  line `years or such less punishment as is in this Act mentioned.`
obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_57:
  sectionId (21689)
  sectionNo (57)
  orderNo 57
  title `Falsifying official documents and false declaration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_57_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=21689&sectionno=57&orderno=57&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_57_content:
  string
  line `Any person subject to this Act who`
  line `commits any of the following offences, that is to say,--`
  line
  line `(a) in any report, return, list, certificate, book or other document made or signed by him, or of the`
  line `contents of which it is his duty to ascertain the accuracy, knowingly makes, or is privy to the making`
  line `of, any false or fraudulent statement; or`
  line
  line `(b) in any document of the description mentioned in clause (a) knowingly makes, or is privy to`
  line `the making of, any omission, with intent to defraud; or`
  line
  line `(c) knowingly and with intent to injure any person, or knowingly and with intent to defraud,`
  line `suppresses, defaces, alters or makes away with any document which it is his duty to preserve or`
  line `produce; or`
  line
  line `(d) where it is his official duty to make a declaration respecting any matter, knowingly makes a`
  line `false declaration; or`
  line
  line `(e) obtains for himself, or for any other person, any pension, allowance or other advantage or`
  line `privilege by a statement which is false, and which he either knows or believes to be false or does not`
  line `believe to be true, or by making or using a false entry in any book or record, or by making any`
  line `document containing a false statement, or by omitting to make a true entry or document containing a`
  line `true statement;`
  line
  line `shall, on conviction by court-martial, be liable to suffer imprisonment for a term which may extend to`
  line `fourteen years or such less punishment as is in this Act mentioned.`
obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_58:
  sectionId (21690)
  sectionNo (58)
  orderNo 58
  title `Signing in blank and failure to report.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_58_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=21690&sectionno=58&orderno=58&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_58_content:
  string
  line `Any person subject to this Act who commits any of the`
  line `following offences, that is to say,--`
  line
  line `(a) when signing any document relating to pay, arms, ammunition, equipment, clothing, supplies`
  line `or stores, or any property of the Government fraudulently leaves in blank any material part for which`
  line `his signature is a voucher; or`
  line
  line `(b) refuses or by culpable neglect omits to make or send a report or return which it is his duty to`
  line `make or send;`
  line
  line `shall, on conviction by court-martial, be liable to suffer imprisonment for a term which may extend to`
  line `seven years or such less punishment as is in this Act mentioned.`
obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_59:
  sectionId (21691)
  sectionNo (59)
  orderNo 59
  title `Offences relating to courts-martial.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_59_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=21691&sectionno=59&orderno=59&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_59_content:
  string
  line `Any person subject to this Act who commits any of the`
  line `following offences, that is to say,--`
  line
  line `(a) being duly summoned or ordered to attend as a witness before a court- martial, wilfully or`
  line `without reasonable excuse, makes default in attending; or`
  line
  line `(b) refuses to take an oath or make an affirmation legally required by a court-martial to be taken`
  line `or made; or`
  line
  line `(c) refuses to produce or deliver any document in his power or control legally required by a courtmartial`
  line `to be produced or delivered by him; or`
  line
  line `(d) refuses when a witness to answer any question which he is by law bound to answer; or`
  line
  line `(e) is guilty of contempt of court-martial by using insulting or threatening language, or by causing`
  line `any interruption or disturbance in the proceedings of such court;`
  line
  line `shall, on conviction by court-martial, be liable to suffer imprisonment for a term which may extend to`
  line `three years or such less punishment as is in this Act mentioned.`
obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_60:
  sectionId (21692)
  sectionNo (60)
  orderNo 60
  title `False evidence`
  content obj_root_law_sections_60_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=21692&sectionno=60&orderno=60&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_60_content:
  string
  line `Any person subject to this Act who, having been duly sworn or affirmed before`
  line `any court-martial or other court competent under this Act to administer an oath or affirmation, makes any statement which is false, and which he either knows or believes to be false or does not believe to be true,`
  line `shall, on conviction by court-martial, be liable to suffer imprisonment for a term which may extend to`
  line `seven years or such less punishment as is in this Act mentioned.`
obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_61:
  sectionId (21693)
  sectionNo (61)
  orderNo 61
  title `Unlawful detention of pay.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_61_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_61_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=21693&sectionno=61&orderno=61&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_61_content:
  string
  line `Any officer, warrant officer or non-commissioned officer who,`
  line `having received the pay of a person subject to this Act unlawfully detains or refuses to pay the same when`
  line `due, shall, on conviction by court-martial, be liable to suffer imprisonment for a term which may extend`
  line `to ten years or such less punishment as is in this Act mentioned.`
obj_root_law_sections_61_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_62:
  sectionId (21694)
  sectionNo (62)
  orderNo 62
  title `Offences in relation to aircraft and flying`
  content obj_root_law_sections_62_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=21694&sectionno=62&orderno=62&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_62_content:
  string
  line `Any person subject to this Act who commits any of`
  line `the following offences, that is to say,--`
  line
  line `(a) wilfully or without reasonable excuse damages, destroys or loses any aircraft or aircraft`
  line `material belonging to the Government; or`
  line
  line `(b) is guilty of any act or neglect likely to cause such damage, destruction or loss; or`
  line
  line `(c) without lawful authority disposes of any aircraft or aircraft material belonging to the`
  line `Government; or`
  line
  line `(d) is guilty of any act or neglect in flying, or in the use of any aircraft, or in relation to any`
  line `aircraft or aircraft material, which causes or is likely to cause loss of life or bodily injury to any`
  line `person; or`
  line
  line `(e) during a state of war, wilfully and without proper occasion, or negligently, causes the`
  line `sequestration, by or under the authority of a neutral State, or the destruction in a neutral State, of any`
  line `aircraft belonging to the Government;`
  line
  line `shall, on conviction by court-martial, be liable, if he has acted wilfully, to suffer imprisonment for a term`
  line `which may extend to fourteen years or such less punishment as is in this Act mentioned, and, in any other`
  line `case, to suffer imprisonment for a term which may extend to five years or such less punishment as is in`
  line `this Act mentioned.`
obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_63:
  sectionId (21695)
  sectionNo (63)
  orderNo 63
  title `Other offences relating to aircraft and flying.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_63_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 19 of 1955, s. 2 and the Schedule, for "the Commander-in-Chief", (w.e.f. 7-5-1955).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=21695&sectionno=63&orderno=63&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_63_content:
  string
  line `Any person subject to this Act who commits`
  line `any of the following offences, that is to say,--`
  line
  line `(a) signs any certificate in relation to an aircraft material belonging to the Government without`
  line `ensuring the accuracy thereof; or`
  line
  line `(b) being the pilot of an aircraft belonging to the Government, flies it at a height less than such`
  line `height as may be specified by ^1[the Chief of the Air Staff], except while taking off or landing, or in`
  line `such other circumstances as may be specified by ^1[the Chief of the Air Staff)]; or`
  line
  line `(c) being the pilot of an aircraft belonging to the Government, flies it so as to cause, or to be`
  line `likely to cause, unnecessary annoyance to any person;`
  line
  line `shall, on conviction by court-martial, be liable to suffer imprisonment for a term which may extend to two`
  line `years or such less punishment as is in this Act mentioned.`
obj_root_law_sections_64:
  sectionId (21696)
  sectionNo (64)
  orderNo 64
  title `Disobedience of lawful command of captain of aircraft.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_64_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_64_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=21696&sectionno=64&orderno=64&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_64_content:
  string
  line `Any person subject to this Act who,`
  line `whatever his rank, commits any of the following offences, that is to say,--`
  line
  line `(a) while he is in an aircraft disobeys any lawful command given by the captain of the aircraft,`
  line `whether such captain is subject to this Act or not, as respects all matters relating to the flying or`
  line `handling of the aircraft, or affecting the safety thereof; or`
  line
  line `(b) being the captain of a glider aircraft towed by another aircraft disobeys any lawful command`
  line `given by the captain of the towing aircraft, whether the latter is subject to this Act or not, as respects`
  line `all matters aforesaid;`
  line
  line `shall, on conviction by court-martial, be liable to suffer imprisonment for a term which may extend to`
  line `fourteen years or such less punishment as is in this Act mentioned.`
obj_root_law_sections_64_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_65:
  sectionId (21697)
  sectionNo (65)
  orderNo 65
  title `Violation of good order and air force discipline.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_65_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_65_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=21697&sectionno=65&orderno=65&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_65_content:
  string
  line `Any person subject to this Act who is guilty`
  line `of any act or omission which though not specified in this Act, is prejudicial to good order and air force`
  line `discipline shall, on conviction by court-martial, be liable to suffer imprisonment for a term which may`
  line `extend to seven years or such less punishment as is in this Act mentioned.`
obj_root_law_sections_65_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_66:
  sectionId (21698)
  sectionNo (66)
  orderNo 66
  title `Miscellaneous offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_66_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_66_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=21698&sectionno=66&orderno=66&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_66_content:
  string
  line `Any person subject to this Act who commits any of the following`
  line `offences, that is to say,--`
  line
  line `(a) being in command at any post or on the march, and receiving a complaint that any one under`
  line `this command has beaten or otherwise maltreated or oppressed any person, or has disturbed any fair`
  line `or market, or committed any riot or trespass, fails to have due reparation made to the injured person`
  line `or to report the case to the proper authority; or`
  line
  line `(b) by defiling any place of worship, or otherwise, intentionally insults the religion or wounds the`
  line `religious feelings of any person; or`
  line
  line `(c) attempts to commit suicide, and in such attempt does any act towards the commission of such`
  line `offence; or`
  line
  line `(d) being below the rank of warrant officer, when off duty, appears, without proper authority, in`
  line `or about camp or cantonments, or in or about, or when going to or returning from, any town or bazar,`
  line `carrying a rifle, sword or other offensive weapon; or`
  line
  line `(e) directly or indirectly accepts or obtains, or agrees to accept or attempts to obtain, for himself`
  line `or for any other person, any gratification as a motive or reward for procuring the enrolment of any`
  line `person, or leave of absence, promotion or any other advantage or indulgence for any person in the`
  line `service; or`
  line
  line `(f) commits any offence against the property or person of any inhabitant of, or resident in, the`
  line `country in which he is serving;`
  line
  line `shall, on conviction by court-martial, be liable to suffer imprisonment for a term which may extend to`
  line `seven years or such less punishment as is in this Act mentioned.`
obj_root_law_sections_66_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_67:
  sectionId (21699)
  sectionNo (67)
  orderNo 67
  title Attempt.
  content obj_root_law_sections_67_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_67_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=21699&sectionno=67&orderno=67&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_67_content:
  string
  line `Any person subject to this Act who attempts to commit any of the offences specified`
  line `in sections 34 to 66 inclusive, and in such attempt does any act towards the commission of the offence`
  line `shall, on conviction by court-martial, where no express provision is made by this Act for the punishment`
  line `of such attempt, be liable,`
  line
  line `if the offence attempted to be committed is punishable with death, to suffer imprisonment for a term`
  line `which may extend to fourteen years or such less punishment as is in this Act mentioned; and`
  line
  line `if the offence attempted to be committed is punishable with imprisonment, to suffer imprisonment for a`
  line `term which may extend to one-half of the longest term provided for that offence or such less punishment`
  line `as is in this Act mentioned.`
obj_root_law_sections_67_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_68:
  sectionId (21700)
  sectionNo (68)
  orderNo 68
  title `Abetment of offences that have been committed.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_68_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_68_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=21700&sectionno=68&orderno=68&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_68_content:
  string
  line `Any person subject to this Act who abets`
  line `the commission of any of the offences specified in sections 34 to 66 inclusive, shall, on conviction by`
  line `court-martial, if the act abetted is committed in consequence of the abetment and no express provision is`
  line `made by this Act for the punishment of such abetment, be liable to suffer the punishment provided for`
  line `that offence or such less punishment as is in this Act mentioned.`
obj_root_law_sections_68_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_69:
  sectionId (21701)
  sectionNo (69)
  orderNo 69
  title `Abetment of offences punishable with death and not committed.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_69_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_69_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=21701&sectionno=69&orderno=69&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_69_content:
  string
  line `Any person subject to this`
  line `Act who abets the commission of any of the offences punishable with death under sections 34, 37 and`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 38 shall, on conviction by court-martial, if that offence be not committed in`
  line `consequence of the abetment, and no express provision is made by this Act for the punishment of such`
  line `abetment, be liable to suffer imprisonment for a term which may extend to fourteen years or such less`
  line `punishment as is in this Act mentioned.`
obj_root_law_sections_69_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_70:
  sectionId (21702)
  sectionNo (70)
  orderNo 70
  title `Abetment of offences punishable with imprisonment and not committed.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_70_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_70_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=21702&sectionno=70&orderno=70&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_70_content:
  string
  line `Any person`
  line `subject to this Act who abets the commission of any of the offences specified in sections 34 to 66`
  line `inclusive and punishable with imprisonment shall, on conviction by court-martial, if that offence be not`
  line `committed in consequence of the abetment, and no express provision is made by this Act for the`
  line `punishment of such abetment, be liable to suffer imprisonment for a term which may extend to one-half`
  line `of the longest term provided for that offence or such less punishment as is in this Act mentioned.`
obj_root_law_sections_70_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_71:
  sectionId (21703)
  sectionNo (71)
  orderNo 71
  title `Civil offences`
  content obj_root_law_sections_71_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_71_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=21703&sectionno=71&orderno=71&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_71_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of section 72, any person subject to this Act who at any`
  line `place in or beyond India commits any civil offence shall be deemed to be guilty of an offence against this`
  line `Act and, if charged therewith under this section shall be liable to be tried by a court-martial and, on`
  line `conviction, be punishable as follows, that is to say,--`
  line
  line `(a) if the offence is one which would be punishable under any law in force in India with death or`
  line `with transportation, he shall be liable to suffer any punishment, other than whipping, assigned for the`
  line `offence, by the aforesaid law and such less punishment as is in this Act mentioned; and`
  line
  line `(b) in any other case, he shall be liable to suffer any punishment other than whipping assigned`
  line `for the offence by any law in force in India, or imprisonment for a term which may extend to seven`
  line `years or such less punishment as is in this Act mentioned.`
obj_root_law_sections_71_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_72:
  sectionId (21704)
  sectionNo (72)
  orderNo 72
  title `Civil offences not triable by court-martial.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_72_content
  footnotes `1. The Explanation omitted by Act 13 of 1975, s. 2 (w.e.f. 25-1-1975).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=21704&sectionno=72&orderno=72&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_72_content:
  string
  line `A person subject to this Act who commits an`
  line `offence of murder against a person not subject to military, naval or air force law, or of culpable homicide`
  line `not amounting to murder against such a person or of rape in relation to such a person, shall not be deemed`
  line `to be guilty of an offence against this Act and shall not be tried by a court-martial, unless he commits any`
  line `of the said offences`
  line
  line `(a) while on active service, or`
  line
  line `(b) at any place outside India, or`
  line
  line `(c) at a frontier post specified by the said Government by notification in this behalf.`
  line
  line `^1* * * * *`
obj_root_law_sections_73:
  sectionId (21705)
  sectionNo (73)
  orderNo 73
  title `Punishments awardable by courts-martial.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_73_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_73_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=21705&sectionno=73&orderno=73&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_73_content:
  string
  line `Punishments may be inflicted in respect of`
  line `offences committed by persons subject to this Act and convicted by courts-martial according to the scale`
  line `following, that is to say,--`
  line
  line `(a) death;`
  line
  line `(b) transportation for life or for any period not less than seven years, in respect of civil offences;`
  line
  line `(c) imprisonment, either rigorous or simple, for any period not exceeding fourteen years;`
  line
  line `(d) detention for a term not exceeding two years in the case of airmen;`
  line
  line `(e) cashiering, in the case of officers;`
  line
  line `(f) dismissal from service;`
  line
  line `(g) reduction to the ranks or to a lower rank or classification, in the case of warrant officers and`
  line `non-commissioned officers:`
  line
  line `Provided that a warrant officer reduced to the ranks shall not be required to serve in the ranks as`
  line `an airman;`
  line
  line `(h) forfeiture of seniority of rank, in the case of officers, warrant officers and non-commissioned`
  line `officers; and forfeiture of all or any part of their service for the purpose of promotion, in the case of`
  line `any of them whose promotion depends upon length of service;`
  line
  line `(i) forfeiture of service for the purpose of increased pay, pension or any other prescribed purpose;`
  line
  line `(j) severe reprimand or reprimand, in the case of officers, warrant officers and non-commissioned`
  line officers;
  line
  line `(k) forfeiture of pay and allowances for a period not exceeding three months for an offence`
  line `committed on active service;`
  line
  line `(l) forfeiture, in the case of a person sentenced to cashiering or dismissal from the service of all`
  line `arrears of pay and allowances and other public money due to him at the time of such cashiering or`
  line dismissal;
  line
  line `(m) stoppage of pay and allowances until any proved loss or damage occasioned by the offence of`
  line `which he is convicted is made good.`
obj_root_law_sections_73_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_74:
  sectionId (21706)
  sectionNo (74)
  orderNo 74
  title `Alternative punishments awardable by court-martial.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_74_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_74_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=21706&sectionno=74&orderno=74&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_74_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of this Act, a`
  line `court-martial may, on convicting a person subject to this Act of any of the offences specified in sections`
  line `34 to 70 inclusive, award either the particular punishment with which the offence is stated in the said sections to be punishable, or, in lieu thereof, any one of the punishments lower in the scale set out in`
  line `section 73, regard being had to the nature and degree of the offence.`
obj_root_law_sections_74_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_75:
  sectionId (21707)
  sectionNo (75)
  orderNo 75
  title `Combination of punishments.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_75_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_75_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=21707&sectionno=75&orderno=75&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_75_content:
  string
  line `A sentence of a court-martial may award in addition to, or`
  line `without any one other punishment, the punishment specified in clause (e) or clause (f) of section 73 and`
  line `any one or more of the punishments specified in clauses (g) to (m) of that section.`
obj_root_law_sections_75_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_76:
  sectionId (21708)
  sectionNo (76)
  orderNo 76
  title `Cashiering of officers`
  content obj_root_law_sections_76_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_76_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=21708&sectionno=76&orderno=76&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_76_content:
  string
  line `An officer shall be sentenced to be cashiered before he is awarded any`
  line `of the punishments specified in clauses (a) to (c) of section 73.`
obj_root_law_sections_76_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_77:
  sectionId (21709)
  sectionNo (77)
  orderNo 77
  title `Field punishment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_77_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_77_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=21709&sectionno=77&orderno=77&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_77_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where any person subject to this Act and under the rank of warrant`
  line `officer commits any offence on active service, shall be lawful for a court-martial to award for that offence`
  line `any such punishment as is prescribed as a field punishment.`
  line
  line `(2) Field punishment shall be of the character of personal restraint or of hard labour but shall not be`
  line `of a nature to cause injury to life or limb and shall not include flogging.`
obj_root_law_sections_77_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_78:
  sectionId (21710)
  sectionNo (78)
  orderNo 78
  title `Position of field punishment in scale of punishments`
  content obj_root_law_sections_78_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_78_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=21710&sectionno=78&orderno=78&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_78_content:
  string
  line `Field punishment shall for the purpose`
  line `of commutation be deemed to stand next below dismissal in the scale of punishments specified in section`
  line 73.
obj_root_law_sections_78_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_79:
  sectionId (21711)
  sectionNo (79)
  orderNo 79
  title `Result of certain punishments in the case of a warrant officer or a non-commissioned officer`
  content obj_root_law_sections_79_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_79_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=21711&sectionno=79&orderno=79&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_79_content:
  string
  line `A warrant officer or a non-commissioned officer sentenced by a court-martial to transportation,`
  line `imprisonment, detention, field punishment or dismissal from the service shall be deemed to be reduced to`
  line `the ranks.`
obj_root_law_sections_79_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_80:
  sectionId (21712)
  sectionNo (80)
  orderNo 80
  title `Retention in the ranks of a person convicted on active service.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_80_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_80_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=21712&sectionno=80&orderno=80&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_80_content:
  string
  line `When, on active service, any`
  line `enrolled person has been sentenced by a court-martial to dismissal, or to transportation, imprisonment or`
  line `detention, whether combined with dismissal or not, the prescribed officer may direct that such person may`
  line `be retained to serve in the ranks and such service shall be reckoned as part of his term of transportation,`
  line `imprisonment or detention, if any.`
obj_root_law_sections_80_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_81:
  sectionId (21713)
  sectionNo (81)
  orderNo 81
  title `Punishments otherwise than by court-martial`
  content obj_root_law_sections_81_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_81_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=21713&sectionno=81&orderno=81&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_81_content:
  string
  line `Punishments may, also be inflicted in respect`
  line `of offences committed by persons, subject to this Act without the intervention of a court-martial and in`
  line `the manner stated in sections 82 and 86.`
obj_root_law_sections_81_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_82:
  sectionId (21714)
  sectionNo (82)
  orderNo 82
  title `Punishment of persons other than officers and warrant officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_82_content
  footnotes `1. Subs by Act 19 of 1955, s. 2 and the Schedule, for "the Commander-in Chief" (w.e.f. 7-5-1955).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=21714&sectionno=82&orderno=82&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_82_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of`
  line `section 84, a commanding officer or such other officer as is, with the consent of the Central Government,`
  line `specified by ^1[the Chief of the Air Staff], may, in the prescribed manner, proceed against a person subject`
  line `to this Act otherwise than as an officer or warrant officer who is charged with an offence under this Act`
  line `and award such person, to the extent prescribed, one or more of the following punishments, that is to`
  line say,--
  line
  line `(a) detention up to twenty-eight days;`
  line
  line `(b) confinement to the camp up to fourteen days;`
  line
  line `(c) extra guards or duties not exceeding three in number:`
  line
  line `(d) deprivation of acting rank;`
  line
  line `(e) forfeiture of badge pay;`
  line
  line `(f) severe reprimand or reprimand;`
  line
  line `(g) fine up to fourteen days' pay in any one month;`
  line
  line `(h) penal deductions under clause`
  line
  line `(g) of section 92;`
  line
  line `(i) admonition;`
  line
  line `(j) any prescribed field punishment up to twenty-eight days, in the case of a person on active`
  line service.
obj_root_law_sections_83:
  sectionId (21715)
  sectionNo (83)
  orderNo 83
  title `Requirement of sanction in certain cases`
  content obj_root_law_sections_83_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_83_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=21715&sectionno=83&orderno=83&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_83_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of sub-section (2), the`
  line `punishments mentioned in section 82 shall not be inflicted in respect of an offence under any of the`
  line `sections 34, 35 and 36 when committed on active service or under any of the sections 37, 38, 40, 42 (f)`
  line `and (g), 43, 47, 52, 60, 62, 63, 64, 66(a), (b) and (c) and 71 except with the previous sanction in writing`
  line `of an officer having power to convene a district court-martial.`
  line
  line `(2) The said punishments may be awarded without such sanction in the case of any offence other than`
  line `an offence under section 34 or section 71, committed by persons who have not been enrolled as`
  line combatants.
obj_root_law_sections_83_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_84:
  sectionId (21716)
  sectionNo (84)
  orderNo 84
  title `Limit of punishments under section 82.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_84_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_84_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=21716&sectionno=84&orderno=84&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_84_content:
  string
  line `(1) An Award of punishment under section 82 shall`
  line `not include field punishment in addition to one or more of the punishments specified in clauses (a) and`
  line `(b) of that section.`
  line
  line `(2) In the case of an award of two or more of the punishments specified in clauses (a), (b) and (c) of`
  line `the said section, the punishment specified in clause (b) or clause (c) shall take effect only at the end of the`
  line `punishment specified in clause (a).`
  line
  line `(3) When two or more of the punishments specified in the said clauses (a) and (b) are awarded to a`
  line `person conjointly, or when already undergoing one or more of the said punishments, the whole extent of`
  line `the punishments shall not exceed in the aggregate forty-two days.`
  line
  line `(4) The punishments specified in clauses (a), (b), (c), (e), (g) and (j) of section 82 shall not be`
  line `awarded to any person who is of the rank of non-commissioned officer or was, at the time of committing`
  line `the offence for which he is punished, of such rank.`
  line
  line `(5) The punishments specified in clause (f) of the said section shall not be awarded to any person`
  line `below the rank of a non-commissioned officer.`
obj_root_law_sections_84_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_85:
  sectionId (21717)
  sectionNo (85)
  orderNo 85
  title `Punishments in addition to those specified in section 82`
  content obj_root_law_sections_85_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 19 of 1955, s. 2 and the Schedule, for "the Commander-in-Chief"(w.e.f. 7-5-1955).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=21717&sectionno=85&orderno=85&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_85_content:
  string
  line `^1[The Chief of the Air Staff] may,`
  line `with the consent of the Central Government, specify such other punishments as may be awarded under`
  line `section 82 in addition to or without any of the punishments specified in the said section, and the extent to`
  line `which such other punishments may be awarded.`
obj_root_law_sections_86:
  sectionId (21718)
  sectionNo (86)
  orderNo 86
  title `Punishment of officers and warrant officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_86_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 19 of 1955, s. 2 and the Schedule, for "the Commander-in-Chief"(w.e.f. 7-5-1955).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=21718&sectionno=86&orderno=86&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_86_content:
  string
  line `An officer having power to convene a general`
  line `court-martial or such other officer as is, with the consent of the Central Government, specified by ^1[the`
  line `Chief of the Air Staff] may, in the prescribed, manner proceed against an officer below the rank of`
  line `squadron leader or warrant officer, who is charged with an offence under this Act, and award one or more`
  line `of the following punishments, that is to say,--`
  line
  line `(a) forfeiture of seniority, or in the case of any of them whose promotion depends upon length of`
  line `service, forfeiture of service for the purpose of promotion for a period not exceeding twelve months,`
  line `but subject to the right of the accused previous to the award to elect to be tried by a court-martial;`
  line
  line `(b) severe reprimand or reprimand;`
  line
  line `(c) stoppage of pay and allowance until any proved loss or damage occasioned by the offence of`
  line `which he is convicted is made good but subject to the right of the accused specified in clause (a);`
  line
  line `(d) forfeiture of pay and allowances for a period not exceeding three months for an offence under`
  line `clause (e) of section 42 in so far as it consists of neglect to obey flying orders or under section 62 or`
  line `section 63.`
obj_root_law_sections_87:
  sectionId (21719)
  sectionNo (87)
  orderNo 87
  title `Transmission of proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_87_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_87_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=21719&sectionno=87&orderno=87&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_87_content:
  string
  line `In every case in which punishment has been awarded under`
  line `section 86, certified true copies of the proceedings shall be forwarded, in the prescribed manner, by the`
  line `officer awarding the punishment, to a superior air force authority as defined in section 89.`
obj_root_law_sections_87_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_88:
  sectionId (21720)
  sectionNo (88)
  orderNo 88
  title `Review of proceedings`
  content obj_root_law_sections_88_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_88_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=21720&sectionno=88&orderno=88&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_88_content:
  string
  line `If any punishment awarded under section 86 appears to a superior air`
  line `force authority as defined in section 89 to be illegal, unjust or excessive, such authority may cancel, vary`
  line `or remit the punishment and make such other direction as may be appropriate in the circumstances of the`
  line case.
obj_root_law_sections_88_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_89:
  sectionId (21721)
  sectionNo (89)
  orderNo 89
  title `Superior air force authority`
  content obj_root_law_sections_89_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 19 of 1955, s. 2 and the Schedule, for "the Commander-in-Chief" (w.e.f. 7-5-1955).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=21721&sectionno=89&orderno=89&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_89_content:
  string
  line `For the purposes of sections 87 and 88, a "superior air force`
  line `authority" means--`
  line
  line `(a) in the case of punishments awarded by a commanding officer, any officer superior in`
  line `command to such commanding officer;`
  line
  line `(b) in the case of punishments awarded by any other authority, the Central Government, ^1[the`
  line `Chief of the Air Staff] or other officer specified by ^1[the Chief of the Air Staff].`
obj_root_law_sections_90:
  sectionId (21722)
  sectionNo (90)
  orderNo 90
  title `Collective fines.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_90_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_90_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=21722&sectionno=90&orderno=90&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_90_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whenever any weapon or part of a weapon forming part of the equipment`
  line `of a unit or detachment is lost or stolen, the officer commanding such unit or detachment may, after`
  line `obtaining the report of a Court of inquiry, impose a collective fine upon the warrant officers,`
  line `non-commissioned officers and men of such unit, or upon so many of them as, in his judgment, should be`
  line `held responsible for such loss, or theft.`
  line
  line `(2) Such fine shall be assessed as a percentage on the pay of the individuals on whom it falls.`
obj_root_law_sections_90_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_91:
  sectionId (21723)
  sectionNo (91)
  orderNo 91
  title `Deductions from pay and allowances of officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_91_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 19 of 1955, s. 2 and the Schedule, for "the Commander-in-Chief" (w.e.f. 7-5-1955).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=21723&sectionno=91&orderno=91&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_91_content:
  string
  line `The following penal deductions may be`
  line `made from the pay and allowances of an officer, that is to say,--`
  line
  line `(a) all pay and allowances due to an officer for every day he absents himself without leave, unless`
  line `a satisfactory explanation has been given to his commanding officer and has been approved by the`
  line `Central Government;`
  line
  line `(b) all pay and allowances for everyday while he is in custody or under suspension from duty on a`
  line `charge for an offence of which he is afterwards convicted by a criminal court or a court-martial or by`
  line `an officer exercising authority under section 86;`
  line
  line `(c) any sum required to make good the pay of any person subject to this Act which he has`
  line `unlawfully retained or unlawfully refused to pay;`
  line
  line `(d) any sum required to make good such compensation for any expenses, loss, damage or`
  line `destruction occasioned by the commission of an offence as may be determined by the court-martial`
  line `by whom he is convicted of such offence, or by an officer exercising authority under section 86;`
  line
  line `(e) all pay and allowances ordered by a court-martial or an officer exercising authority under`
  line `section 86 to be forfeited or stopped;`
  line
  line `(f) any sum required to pay a fine awarded by a criminal court or a court-martial exercising`
  line `jurisdiction under section 71;`
  line
  line `(g) any sum required to make good any loss, damage or destruction of public or service property`
  line `which, after due investigation, appears to the Central Government to have been occasioned by the`
  line `wrongful act or negligence on the part of the officer;`
  line
  line `(h) all pay and allowances forfeited by order of the Central Government if the officer is found by`
  line `a court of inquiry constituted by ^1[the Chief of the Air Staff] in this behalf, to have deserted to the`
  line `enemy, or while in enemy hands, to have served with, or under the orders of, the enemy or in any`
  line `manner to have aided the enemy, or to have allowed himself to be taken prisoner by the enemy`
  line `through want of due precaution or through disobedience of orders or wilful neglect of duty, or having`
  line `been taken prisoner by the enemy to have failed to rejoin his service when it was possible to do so;`
  line
  line `(i) any sum required by order of the Central Government to be paid for the maintenance of his`
  line `wife or his legitimate or illegitimate child or towards the costs of any relief given by the said`
  line `Government to the said wife or child.`
obj_root_law_sections_92:
  sectionId (28936)
  sectionNo (92)
  orderNo 92
  title `Deductions from pay and allowances of airmen`
  content obj_root_law_sections_92_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_92_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=28936&sectionno=92&orderno=92&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_92_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of section 95, the`
  line `following penal deductions may be made from the pay and allowances of an airman, that is to say,--`
  line
  line `(a) all pay and allowances for every day of absence either on desertion or without leave, or as a`
  line `prisoner of war, and for every day of transportation or imprisonment awarded by a criminal court, or`
  line `a court-martial, or of detention, or field punishment awarded by a court-martial or an officer`
  line `exercising authority under section 82;`
  line
  line `(b) all pay and allowances for every day while he is in custody on a charge for an offence of`
  line `which he is afterwards convicted by a criminal court or a court-martial, or on a charge of absence`
  line `without leave for which he is afterwards awarded detention or field punishment by an officer`
  line `exercising authority under section 82;`
  line
  line `(c) all pay and allowances for every day on which he is in hospital on account of sickness`
  line `certified by the medical officer attending on him to have been caused by an offence under this Act`
  line `committed by him;`
  line
  line `(d) for every day on which he is in hospital on account of sickness certified by the medical officer`
  line `attending on him to have been caused by his own misconduct or imprudence, such sum as may be specified by order of the Central Government or by such officer as may be specified by that`
  line Government;
  line
  line `(e) all pay and allowances ordered by a court-martial or by an officer exercising authority under`
  line `section 82 or section 86 to be forfeited or stopped;`
  line
  line `(f) all pay and allowances for every day between his being recovered from the enemy and his`
  line `dismissal from the service in consequence of his conduct when being taken prisoner by, or while in`
  line `the hands of, the enemy;`
  line
  line `(g) any sum required to make good such compensation for any expenses, loss, damage or`
  line `destruction caused by him to the Central Government or to any building or property as may be`
  line `awarded by his commanding officer;`
  line
  line `(h) any sum require to pay a fine awarded by a criminal court, a court-martial exercising`
  line `jurisdiction under section 71, or an officer exercising authority under section 82 or section 90.`
  line
  line `(i) any sum required by order of the Central Government or any prescribed officer to be paid for`
  line `the maintenance of his wife or his legitimate or illegitimate child or towards the cost of any relief`
  line `given by the said Government to the said wife or child.`
obj_root_law_sections_92_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_93:
  sectionId (28937)
  sectionNo (93)
  orderNo 93
  title `Computation of time of absence of custody.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_93_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_93_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=28937&sectionno=93&orderno=93&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_93_content:
  string
  line `For the purposes of clauses (a) and (b) of`
  line `section 92--`
  line
  line `(a) no person shall be treated as absent or in custody for a day unless the absence or custody has`
  line `lasted, whether wholly in one day, or partly in one day and partly in another, for six consecutive`
  line `hours or upwards;`
  line
  line `(b) any absence or custody for less than a day may be reckoned as absence or custody for a day if`
  line `such absence or custody prevented the absence from fulfilling any air force duty which was thereby`
  line `thrown upon some other person;`
  line
  line `(c) absence or custody for twelve consecutive hours or upwards may be reckoned as absence or`
  line `custody for the whole of each day during any portion of which the person was absent or in custody;`
  line
  line `(d) a period of absence, or imprisonment, which commences before and ends after midnight may`
  line `be reckoned as a day.`
obj_root_law_sections_93_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_94:
  sectionId (28938)
  sectionNo (94)
  orderNo 94
  title `Pay and allowances daring trial.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_94_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_94_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=28938&sectionno=94&orderno=94&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_94_content:
  string
  line `In the case of any person subject to this Act who is in`
  line `custody or under suspension from duty on a charge for an offence, the prescribed officer may direct that`
  line `the whole or any part of the pay and allowances of such person shall be withheld, pending the result of his`
  line `trial in the charge against him, in order to give effect to the provisions of clause (b) of sections 91 and 92.`
obj_root_law_sections_94_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_95:
  sectionId (28939)
  sectionNo (95)
  orderNo 95
  title `Limit of certain deductions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_95_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_95_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=28939&sectionno=95&orderno=95&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_95_content:
  string
  line `The total deductions from the pay and allowances of a person`
  line `made under clauses (e) and (g) to (i) of section 92 shall not, except where he is sentenced to dismissal,`
  line `exceed in any one month one-half of his pay and allowances for that month.`
obj_root_law_sections_95_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_96:
  sectionId (28940)
  sectionNo (96)
  orderNo 96
  title `Deduction from public money due to a person.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_96_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_96_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=28940&sectionno=96&orderno=96&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_96_content:
  string
  line `Any sum authorised by this Act to be`
  line `deducted from the pay and allowances of any person may, without prejudice to any other mode of`
  line `recovering the same, be deducted from any public money due to him other than a pension.`
obj_root_law_sections_96_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_97:
  sectionId (28941)
  sectionNo (97)
  orderNo 97
  title `Pay and allowances of prisoner of war during inquiry into his conduct.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_97_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 19 of 1955, s. 2 and the Schedule, for "the Commander-in-Chief" (w.e.f. 7-5-1955).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=28941&sectionno=97&orderno=97&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_97_content:
  string
  line `Where the conduct`
  line `of any person subject to this Act when being taken prisoner by, or while in the hands of the enemy, is to`
  line `be inquired into under this Act or any other law, ^1[the Chief of the Air Staff] or any officer authorised by`
  line `him may order that the whole or any part of the pay and allowances of such person shall be withheld`
  line `pending the result of such inquiry.`
obj_root_law_sections_98:
  sectionId (28942)
  sectionNo (98)
  orderNo 98
  title `Remission of deductions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_98_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_98_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=28942&sectionno=98&orderno=98&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_98_content:
  string
  line `Any deduction from pay and allowances authorised by this Act may`
  line `be remitted in such manner, and to such extent, and by such authority, as may from time to time be`
  line prescribed.
obj_root_law_sections_98_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_99:
  sectionId (28943)
  sectionNo (99)
  orderNo 99
  title `Provision for dependants of prisoner of war from remitted deductions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_99_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_99_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=28943&sectionno=99&orderno=99&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_99_content:
  string
  line `In the case of all`
  line `persons subject to this Act, being prisoners of war, whose pay and allowances have been forfeited under`
  line `clause (h) of section 91 or clause (a) of section 92, but in respect of whom a remission has been made`
  line `under section 98, it shall be lawful for proper provision to be made by the prescribed authorities out of`
  line `such pay and allowances for any dependants of such persons, and any such remission shall in that case be`
  line `deemed to apply only to the balance thereafter remaining of such pay and allowances.'`
obj_root_law_sections_99_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_100:
  sectionId (28944)
  sectionNo (100)
  orderNo 100
  title `Provision for dependants of prisoner of war from his pay and allowances.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_100_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_100_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=28944&sectionno=100&orderno=100&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_100_content:
  string
  line `It shall be`
  line `lawful for proper provision to be made by the prescribed authorities for any dependants of any person`
  line `subject to this Act, who is a prisoner of war or is missing, out of his pay and allowances.`
obj_root_law_sections_100_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_101:
  sectionId (28945)
  sectionNo (101)
  orderNo 101
  title `Period during which a person is deemed to be a prisoner of war`
  content obj_root_law_sections_101_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_101_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=28945&sectionno=101&orderno=101&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_101_content:
  string
  line `For the purposes of`
  line `sections 99 and 100, a person shall be deemed to continue to be a prisoner of war until the conclusion of`
  line `any inquiry into has conduct such as is referred to in section 97, and if he is cashiered or dismissed from`
  line `the service in consequence of such conduct, until the date of such cashiering or dismissal.`
obj_root_law_sections_101_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_102:
  sectionId (28946)
  sectionNo (102)
  orderNo 102
  title `Custody of offenders`
  content obj_root_law_sections_102_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_102_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=28946&sectionno=102&orderno=102&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_102_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person subject to this Act who is charged with an offence may`
  line `be taken into air force custody.`
  line
  line `(2) Any such person may be ordered into air force custody by any superior officer.`
  line
  line `(3) Any officer may order into air force custody any officer, though he may be of a higher rank,`
  line `engaged in a quarrel, affray or disorder.`
obj_root_law_sections_102_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_103:
  sectionId (28947)
  sectionNo (103)
  orderNo 103
  title `Duty of commanding officer in regard to detention.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_103_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_103_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=28947&sectionno=103&orderno=103&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_103_content:
  string
  line `(1) It shall be the duty of every`
  line `commanding officer to take care that a person under his command when charged with an offence is not`
  line `detained in custody for more than forty-eight hours after the committal of such person into custody is`
  line `reported to him, without the charge being investigated, unless investigation within that period seems to`
  line `him to be impracticable with due regard to the public service.`
  line
  line `(2) Every case of a person being detained in custody beyond a period of forty eight hours, and the`
  line `reason thereof shall be reported by the commanding officer to the air or other officer to whom application`
  line `would be made to convene a general or district court-martial for the trial of the person charged.`
  line
  line `(3) In reckoning the period of forty-eight hours specified in sub-section (1), Sundays and public`
  line `holidays shall be excluded.`
  line
  line `(4) Subject to the provisions of this Act, the Central Government may make rules a providing for the`
  line `manner in which and the period for which any person subject to this Act may be taken into and detained`
  line `in air force custody, pending the trial by any competent authority for any offence committed by him.`
obj_root_law_sections_103_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_104:
  sectionId (28948)
  sectionNo (104)
  orderNo 104
  title `Interval between committal and court-martial`
  content obj_root_law_sections_104_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_104_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=28948&sectionno=104&orderno=104&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_104_content:
  string
  line `In every case where any such person as is`
  line `mentioned in section 102 and as is not on active service remains in such custody for a longer period than`
  line `eight days, without a court-martial for his trial being ordered to assemble, a special report giving reasons`
  line `for the delay shall be made by his commanding officer in the manner prescribed; and similar report shall`
  line `be forwarded every eight days until a court-martial is assembled or such person is released from custody.`
obj_root_law_sections_104_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_105:
  sectionId (28949)
  sectionNo (105)
  orderNo 105
  title `Arrest by civil authorities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_105_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_105_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=28949&sectionno=105&orderno=105&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_105_content:
  string
  line `Wherever any person subject to this Act, who is accused of any`
  line `offence under this Act, is within the jurisdiction of any magistrate or police officer, such magistrate or`
  line `police officer shall aid in the apprehension and delivery to air force custody of such person upon receipt`
  line `of a written application to that effect signed by his commanding officer.`
obj_root_law_sections_105_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_106:
  sectionId (28950)
  sectionNo (106)
  orderNo 106
  title `Capture of deserters.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_106_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_106_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=28950&sectionno=106&orderno=106&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_106_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whenever any person subject to this Act deserts, the commanding`
  line `officer of the unit or detachment to which he belongs, shall give written information of the desertion to`
  line `such civil authorities as, in his opinion, may be able to afford assistance towards the capture of the`
  line `deserter; and such authorities shall thereupon take steps for the apprehension of the said deserter in like`
  line `manner as if he were a person for whole apprehension a warrant had been issued by a magistrate; and`
  line `shall deliver the deserter, when apprehended, into air force custody.`
  line
  line `(2) Any police officer may arrest without warrant any person reasonably believed to be subject to this`
  line `Act, and to be a deserter or to be travelling without authority, and shall bring him without delay before the`
  line `nearest magistrate, to be dealt with according to law.`
obj_root_law_sections_106_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_107:
  sectionId (28951)
  sectionNo (107)
  orderNo 107
  title `Inquiry into absence without leave.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_107_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_107_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=28951&sectionno=107&orderno=107&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_107_content:
  string
  line `(1) When any person subject to this Act has been absent`
  line `from his duty without due authority for a period of thirty days, a Court of inquiry shall, as soon as`
  line `practicable, be assembled, and such Court shall, on oath or affirmation administered. In the prescribed`
  line `manner, inquire respecting the absence of the person, and the deficiency, if any, in the property of the`
  line `Government entrusted to his care, or in any arms, ammunition, equipment, instruments, clothing or`
  line `necessaries, and if satisfied of the fact of such absence without due authority, or other sufficient cause, the`
  line `Court shall declare such absence and the period thereof, and the said deficiency, if any; and the`
  line `commanding officer of the unit to which the person belongs shall enter in the court-martial book of the`
  line `unit a record of declaration.`
  line
  line `(2) If the person declared absent does not afterwards surrender or is not apprehended, he shall, for the`
  line `purposes of this Act, be deemed to be a deserter.`
obj_root_law_sections_107_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_108:
  sectionId (28952)
  sectionNo (108)
  orderNo 108
  title Provost-marshals.
  content obj_root_law_sections_108_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 19 of 1955, s. 2 and the Schedule, for "the Commander-in-Chief", (w.e.f. 7-5-1955).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=28952&sectionno=108&orderno=108&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_108_content:
  string
  line `(1) Provost-marshals may be appointed by ^1[the Chief of the Air Staff], or`
  line `by any prescribed officer.`
  line
  line `(2) The duties of a provost-marshal are to take charge of persons confined for any offence, to preserve`
  line `good order and discipline, and to prevent breaches of the same by persons serving in, or attached to, the`
  line `Air Force.`
  line
  line `(3) A provost-marshal may at any time arrest and detain for trial any person subject to this Act who`
  line `commits, or is charged with, an offence, and may also carry into effect any punishment to be inflicted in`
  line `pursuance of the sentence awarded by a court-martial, or by an officer exercising authority under section`
  line `82 but shall not inflict any punishment on his own authority:`
  line
  line `Provided that no officer shall be so arrested or detained otherwise than on the order of another officer.`
  line
  line `(4) For the purposes of sub-sections (2) and (3), a provost-marshal shall be deemed to include a`
  line `provost-marshal appointed under the Army Act or the Navy-Act and any person legally exercising`
  line `authority under him or on his behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_109:
  sectionId (28953)
  sectionNo (109)
  orderNo 109
  title `Different kinds of courts-martial.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_109_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_109_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=28953&sectionno=109&orderno=109&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_109_content:
  string
  line `For purposes of this Act there shall be three kinds of`
  line `courts-martial, that is to say,--`
  line
  line `(a) general courts-martial.`
  line
  line `(b) district courts-martial.`
  line
  line `(c) summary general courts-martial.`
obj_root_law_sections_109_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_110:
  sectionId (28954)
  sectionNo (110)
  orderNo 110
  title `Power to convene a general court-martial.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_110_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 19 of 1955, s. 2 and the Schedule, for "the Commander-in-Chief", (w.e.f. 7-5-1955).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=28954&sectionno=110&orderno=110&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_110_content:
  string
  line `A general court-martial may be convened by the`
  line `Central Government or ^1[the Chief of the Air Staff] or by any officer empowered in this behalf by warrant`
  line `of^1[the Chief of the Air Staff].`
obj_root_law_sections_111:
  sectionId (28955)
  sectionNo (111)
  orderNo 111
  title `Power to convene a district court-martial.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_111_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_111_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=28955&sectionno=111&orderno=111&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_111_content:
  string
  line `A district court-martial may be convened by an`
  line `officer having power to convene a general court-martial, or by any officer empowered in this behalf by`
  line `warrant of any such officer.`
obj_root_law_sections_111_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_112:
  sectionId (28956)
  sectionNo (112)
  orderNo 112
  title `Contents of warrants issued under sections 110 and 111`
  content obj_root_law_sections_112_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_112_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=28956&sectionno=112&orderno=112&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_112_content:
  string
  line `A warrant issued under section`
  line `110 or section 111 may contain such restrictions, reservations or conditions as the officer issuing it may`
  line `think fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_112_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_113:
  sectionId (28957)
  sectionNo (113)
  orderNo 113
  title `Power to convene a summary general court-martial.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_113_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 19 of 1955, s. 2 and the Schedule, for "the Commander-in-Chief", (w.e.f. 7-5-1955).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=28957&sectionno=113&orderno=113&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_113_content:
  string
  line `The following authorities shall have`
  line `the power to convene a summary general court-martial, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) an officer empowered in this behalf by an order of the Central Government or of ^1[the Chief`
  line `of the Air Staff];`
  line
  line `(b) on active service, the officer commanding the forces in the field, or any officer empowered by`
  line `him in this behalf;`
  line
  line `(c) an officer commanding any detached portion of the Air Force on active service when, in his`
  line `opinion, it is not practicable with due regard to discipline and the exigencies of the service, that an`
  line `offence should be tried by a general court-martial.`
obj_root_law_sections_114:
  sectionId (28958)
  sectionNo (114)
  orderNo 114
  title `Composition of general court-martial.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_114_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_114_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=28958&sectionno=114&orderno=114&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_114_content:
  string
  line `A general court-martial shall consist of not less than`
  line `five officers, each of whom has held a commission for not less than three whole years and of whom not`
  line `less than four are of a rank not below that of flight-lieutenant.`
obj_root_law_sections_114_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_115:
  sectionId (28959)
  sectionNo (115)
  orderNo 115
  title `Composition of district court-martial.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_115_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_115_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=28959&sectionno=115&orderno=115&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_115_content:
  string
  line `A district court-martial shall consist of not less than`
  line `three officers, each of whom has held a commission for not less than two whole years.`
obj_root_law_sections_115_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_116:
  sectionId (28960)
  sectionNo (116)
  orderNo 116
  title `Composition of summary general court-martial.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_116_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_116_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=28960&sectionno=116&orderno=116&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_116_content:
  string
  line `A summary general court-martial shall`
  line `consist of not less than three officers.`
obj_root_law_sections_116_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_117:
  sectionId (28961)
  sectionNo (117)
  orderNo 117
  title `Dissolution of court-martial.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_117_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_117_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=28961&sectionno=117&orderno=117&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_117_content:
  string
  line `(1) If a court-martial after the commencement of a trial is`
  line `reduced below the minimum number of Officers required by this Act, it shall be dissolved.`
  line
  line `(2) If on account of the illness of the judge advocate or of the accused before the finding, it is`
  line `impossible to continue the trial, a court-martial shall be dissolved.`
  line
  line `(3) The officer who convened a court-martial may dissolve such court-martial if it appears to him that`
  line `the exigencies of the service or the necessities of discipline render it impossible or in expedient to`
  line `continue the said court-martial.`
  line
  line `(4) Where a court-martial is dissolved under this section, the accused may be tried again.`
obj_root_law_sections_117_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_118:
  sectionId (28962)
  sectionNo (118)
  orderNo 118
  title `Powers of general and summary general courts-martial.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_118_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_118_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=28962&sectionno=118&orderno=118&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_118_content:
  string
  line `A general or summary general`
  line `court- martial shall have power to try any person subject to this Act for any offence punishable there in`
  line `and to pass any sentence authorised thereby.`
obj_root_law_sections_118_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_119:
  sectionId (28963)
  sectionNo (119)
  orderNo 119
  title `Powers of district Court-martial.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_119_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_119_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=28963&sectionno=119&orderno=119&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_119_content:
  string
  line `A district court-martial shall have power to try any person`
  line `subject to this Act other than an officer or warrant officer for any offence made punishable therein, and to`
  line `pass any sentence authorised by this Act other than a sentence of death, transportation, or imprisonment`
  line `for a term exceeding two years.`
obj_root_law_sections_119_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_120:
  sectionId (28964)
  sectionNo (120)
  orderNo 120
  title `Prohibition of second trial.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_120_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_120_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=28964&sectionno=120&orderno=120&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_120_content:
  string
  line `When any person subject to this Act has been acquitted or`
  line `convicted of an offence by a court-martial or by a criminal court, or has been dealt with under section 82`
  line `or section 86, he shall not be liable to be tried again for the same offence by a court-martial or dealt with`
  line `under the said sections.`
obj_root_law_sections_120_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_121:
  sectionId (28965)
  sectionNo (121)
  orderNo 121
  title `Period of limitation for trial.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_121_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_121_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=28965&sectionno=121&orderno=121&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_121_content:
  string
  line `(1) Except as provided by sub-section (2), no trial by courtmartial`
  line `of any person subject to this Act for any offence shall be commenced after the expiration of a`
  line `period of three years from the date of such offence.`
  line
  line `(2) The provisions of sub-section (1) shall not apply to a trial for an offence of desertion or fraudulent`
  line `enrolment or for any of the offences mentioned in section 37.`
  line
  line `(3) In the computation of the period of time mentioned in sub-section (1), any time spent by such`
  line `person as a prisoner of war, or in enemy territory, or in evading arrest after the commission of the`
  line `offence, shall be excluded.`
  line
  line `(4) No trial for an offence of desertion, other than desertion on active service or of fraudulent`
  line `enrolment shall be commenced if the person in question, not being an officer, has subsequently to the`
  line `commission of the offence, served continuously in an exemplary manner for not less than three years with`
  line `any portion of the Air Force.`
obj_root_law_sections_121_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_122:
  sectionId (28966)
  sectionNo (122)
  orderNo 122
  title `Liability of offender who ceases to be subject to Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_122_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_122_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=28966&sectionno=122&orderno=122&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_122_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where an offence under this Act`
  line `had been committed by any person while subject to this Act and he has ceased to be so subject, he may be`
  line `taken into and kept in air force custody, and tried and punished for such offence as if he continued to be`
  line `so subject.`
  line
  line `(2) Except as provided by sub-sections (3) and (4), any such person shall not be tried for an offence,`
  line `unless his trial commences within six months after he had ceased to be subject to this Act.`
  line
  line `(3) The provisions of sub-section (2) shall not apply to the trial of any such person for an offence of`
  line `desertion or fraudulent enrolment or for any of the offences mentioned in section 37.`
  line
  line `(4) Nothing contained in sub-section (2) shall affect the jurisdiction of a civil court to try any offence`
  line `triable by such court as well as by a court-martial.`
  line
  line `(5) When a person subject to this Act is sentenced by a court-martial to transportation or`
  line `imprisonment, this Act shall apply to him during the term of his sentence, though he is cashiered or`
  line `dismissed from the Air Force, or has otherwise ceased to be subject to this Act and he may be kept,`
  line `removed, imprisoned and punished as if he continued to be subject to this Act.`
  line
  line `(6) When a person subject to this Act it sentenced by a court-martial to death, this Act shall apply to`
  line `him till the sentence is carried out.`
obj_root_law_sections_122_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_123:
  sectionId (28967)
  sectionNo (123)
  orderNo 123
  title `Place of trial`
  content obj_root_law_sections_123_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_123_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=28967&sectionno=123&orderno=123&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_123_content:
  string
  line `Any person subject to this Act who commits any offence against it may be tried`
  line `and punished for such offence in any place whatever.`
obj_root_law_sections_123_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_124:
  sectionId (28968)
  sectionNo (124)
  orderNo 124
  title `Choice between criminal court and court-martial.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_124_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 19 of 1955, s. 2 and the Schedule, for "the Commander-in-Chief", (w.e.f. 7-5-1955).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=28968&sectionno=124&orderno=124&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_124_content:
  string
  line `When a criminal court and a courtmartial`
  line `have each jurisdiction in respect of an offence, it shall be in the discretion of^1`
  line `[the Chief of the Air`
  line `Staff], the officer commanding any group, wing or station in which the accused prisoner is serving of`
  line `such other officer as may be prescribed to decide before which court the proceedings shall be instituted,`
  line `and, if that officer decides that they should be instituted before a court-martial, to direct that the accused`
  line `person shall be detained in Air force custody.`
obj_root_law_sections_125:
  sectionId (28969)
  sectionNo (125)
  orderNo 125
  title `Power of criminal court to require delivery of offender.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_125_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_125_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=28969&sectionno=125&orderno=125&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_125_content:
  string
  line `(1) When a criminal court having`
  line `jurisdiction is of opinion that proceedings shall be instituted before itself in respect of any alleged`
  line `offence, it may, by written notice, require the officer referred to in section 124 at his option, either to`
  line `deliver over the offender to the nearest Magistrate to be proceeded, against according to law, or to`
  line `postpone proceedings pending a reference to the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) In every such case the said officer shall either deliver over the offender in compliance with the`
  line `requisition, or shall forthwith refer the question as to the court before which the proceedings are to be`
  line `instituted for the determination of the Central Government whose order upon such reference shall be`
  line final.
obj_root_law_sections_125_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_126:
  sectionId (28970)
  sectionNo (126)
  orderNo 126
  title `Successive trials by a criminal, court and a court-martial.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_126_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_126_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=28970&sectionno=126&orderno=126&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_126_content:
  string
  line `(1) A person convicted or`
  line `acquitted by a court-martial may, with the previous sanction of the Central Government, be tried again by`
  line `a criminal court for the same offence, or on the same facts.`
  line
  line `(2) If a person sentenced by a court-martial under this Act or punished under section 82 or section 86`
  line `is afterwards tried and convicted by a criminal court for the same offence or on the same facts, that court`
  line `shall in awarding punishment have regard to the punishment he may already have undergone for the said`
  line offence.
obj_root_law_sections_126_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_127:
  sectionId (28971)
  sectionNo (127)
  orderNo 127
  title `Presiding Officer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_127_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_127_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=28971&sectionno=127&orderno=127&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_127_content:
  string
  line `At every general, district or summary general court-martial the senior`
  line `member shall be the presiding officer.`
obj_root_law_sections_127_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_128:
  sectionId (28972)
  sectionNo (128)
  orderNo 128
  title `Judge Advocate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_128_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_128_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=28972&sectionno=128&orderno=128&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_128_content:
  string
  line `Every general court-martial shall, and every district or summary general`
  line `court-martial may, be attended by a Judge Advocate, who shall be either an officer belonging to the`
  line `department of the Chief Legal Adviser or if no such officer is available, an officer approved by the Chief`
  line `Legal Adviser or any of his deputies.`
obj_root_law_sections_128_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_129:
  sectionId (28973)
  sectionNo (129)
  orderNo 129
  title Challenges
  content obj_root_law_sections_129_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_129_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=28973&sectionno=129&orderno=129&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_129_content:
  string
  line `(1) At all, trials by general, district or summary general courts-martial, as soon as`
  line `the court is assembled, the names of the presiding officer and members shall be read over to the accused`
  line `who shall thereupon be asked whether he objects to being tried by any officer sitting on the court.`
  line
  line `(2) If the accused objects to any such officer, his objection and also the reply thereto of the officer`
  line `objected to, shall be heard and recorded, and the remaining officers of the court shall, in the absence of`
  line `the challenged officer decide on the objection.`
  line
  line `(3) If the objection is allowed by one-half or more of the votes of the officers entitled to vote, the`
  line `objection shall be allowed and the member objected to shall retire, and his vacancy may be filled in the`
  line `prescribed manner by another officer, subject to the same right of the accused to object.`
  line
  line `(4) When no challenge is made, or when challenge has been made and disallowed or the place of`
  line `every officer successfully challenged has been filled by another officer to whom no objection is made or`
  line `allowed, the court shall proceed with the trial.`
obj_root_law_sections_129_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_130:
  sectionId (28974)
  sectionNo (130)
  orderNo 130
  title `Oaths of member, Judge advocate and witness.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_130_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_130_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=28974&sectionno=130&orderno=130&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_130_content:
  string
  line `(1) An oath or affirmation in the prescribed`
  line `manner shall be administered to every member of every court-martial and to the Judge advocate before`
  line `the commencement of the trial.`
  line
  line `(2) Every person giving evidence before a court-martial shall be examined after being duly sworn or`
  line `affirmed in the prescribed form.`
  line
  line `(3) The provisions of sub-section (2) shall not apply where the witness is a child under twelve years`
  line `of age and the court-martial is of opinion that though the witness understands the duty of speaking the`
  line `truth, he does not understand the nature of an oath or affirmation.`
obj_root_law_sections_130_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_131:
  sectionId (28975)
  sectionNo (131)
  orderNo 131
  title `Voting by members`
  content obj_root_law_sections_131_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_131_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=28975&sectionno=131&orderno=131&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_131_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of sub-sections (2) and (3), every decision`
  line `of a court-martial shall be passed by an absolute majority of votes; and where there is an equality of votes`
  line `on either the finding or the sentence, the decision shall be in favour of the accused.`
  line
  line `(2) No sentence of death shall be passed by a general court-martial without the concurrence of at least`
  line `two-thirds of the members of the court.`
  line
  line `(3) No sentence of death shall be passed by a summary general court-martial without the concurrence`
  line `of all the members.`
  line
  line `(4) In matters other than a challenge or the finding or sentence, the presiding officer shall have a`
  line `casting vote.`
obj_root_law_sections_131_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_132:
  sectionId (28976)
  sectionNo (132)
  orderNo 132
  title `General rule as to evidence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_132_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_132_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=28976&sectionno=132&orderno=132&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_132_content:
  string
  line `The Indian Evidence Act, 1872 (1 of 1872), shall subject to the`
  line `provisions of this Act, apply to all proceedings before a court-martial.`
obj_root_law_sections_132_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_133:
  sectionId (28977)
  sectionNo (133)
  orderNo 133
  title `Judicial notice.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_133_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_133_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=28977&sectionno=133&orderno=133&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_133_content:
  string
  line `A court-martial may take judicial notice of any matter within the general air`
  line `force knowledge of the members.`
obj_root_law_sections_133_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_134:
  sectionId (28978)
  sectionNo (134)
  orderNo 134
  title `Summoning witnesses`
  content obj_root_law_sections_134_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_134_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=28978&sectionno=134&orderno=134&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_134_content:
  string
  line `(1) The convening officer, the presiding officer of a court-martial the`
  line `Judge advocate or the commanding officer of the accused person, may, by summons under his hand,`
  line `require the attendance at a time and place to be mentioned in the summons, of any person either to give`
  line `evidence or to produce any document or other thing.`
  line
  line `(2) In the case of a witness amenable to air force authority, the summons shall be sent to his`
  line `commanding officer and such officer shall serve it upon him accordingly.`
  line
  line `(3) In the case of any other witness, the summons shall be sent to the magistrate within whose`
  line `jurisdiction he may be or reside, and such magistrate shall give effect to the summons as if the witness`
  line `were required in the court of such magistrate.`
  line
  line `(4) When a witness is required to produce any particular document or other thing in his possession or`
  line `power, the summons shall describe it with reasonable precision.`
obj_root_law_sections_134_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_135:
  sectionId (28979)
  sectionNo (135)
  orderNo 135
  title `Documents exempted from production.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_135_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_135_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=28979&sectionno=135&orderno=135&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_135_content:
  string
  line `(1) Nothing in section 134 shall be deemed to affect`
  line `the operation of sections 123 and 124 of the Indian Evidence Act, 1872 (1 of 1872), or to apply to any`
  line `letter, postcard, telegram or other document in the custody of the postal or telegraph authorities.`
  line
  line `(2) If any documrnt in such custody is, in the opinion of any district magistrate, chief presidency`
  line `magistrate, High Court or court of session, wanted for the purpose of any court-martial such magistrate or`
  line `court may require the postal or telegraph authorities, as the case may be, to deliver such document to such`
  line `person as such magistrate or court may direct.`
  line
  line `(3) If any such document is, in the opinion of any other magistrate or of any commissioner of police`
  line `or district superintendent of police, wanted for any such purpose, he may require the postal or telegraph`
  line `authorities, as the case may be, to cause search to be made for and to detain such document pending the`
  line `orders of any such district magistrate, chief presidency magistrate or High Court or Court of Session.`
obj_root_law_sections_135_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_136:
  sectionId (28980)
  sectionNo (136)
  orderNo 136
  title `Commissions for examination of witnesses.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_136_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_136_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=28980&sectionno=136&orderno=136&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_136_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whenever, in the course of a trial by courtmartial,`
  line `it appears to the court that the examination of a witness is necessary for the ends of justice, and`
  line `that the attendance of such witness cannot be procured without an amount of delay, expense or`
  line `inconvenience which, in the circumstances of the case, would be unreasonable such court may address the`
  line `Chief Legal Adviser in order that a commission to take the evidence of such witness may be issued.`
  line
  line `(2) The Chief Legal Adviser may then, if he thinks necessary, issue a commission to any district`
  line `magistrate of the first class, within the local limits of whose jurisdiction such witness resides to take the`
  line `evidence of such witness.`
  line
  line `(3) The Magistrate or officer to whom the commission is issued, or, if he is the district magistrate, he`
  line `or such magistrate of the first-class as he appoints, in this behalf, shall proceed to the place where the`
  line `witness is or shall summon the witness before him and shall take down his evidence in the same manner,`
  line `and may for this purpose exercise the same powers, as in trials of warrant-cases under the Code of`
  line `Criminal Procedure, 1898 (5 of 1898), or any corresponding law in force in ^1[the State of Jammu and`
  line Kashmir*],
  line
  line `(4) When the witness resides in a tribal area or in any place outside India the commission may be`
  line `issued in the manner specified in Chapter XL of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1898 (5 of 1898), or of`
  line `any corresponding law in force in ^1[the State of Jammu and Kashmir*].`
  line
  line `(5) In this and the next succeeding section, the expression "Chief Legal Adviser" includes a Deputy`
  line `Chief Legal Adviser.`
obj_root_law_sections_136_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs by A.O. (No. 3), 1956, for "a Part B State" (w.e.f. 7-5-1955).`
  line `*. Vide Notification No. S.O. 3912 (E), dated 30th October, 2019, this Act is made applicable to the Union territory of Jammu`
  line `and Kashmir and the Union territory of Ladakh.`
obj_root_law_sections_137:
  sectionId (28981)
  sectionNo (137)
  orderNo 137
  title `Examination of a witness on commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_137_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_137_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=28981&sectionno=137&orderno=137&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_137_content:
  string
  line `(1) The prosecutor and the accused person in any`
  line `case in which a commission is issued under section 136 may respectively forward any interrogatories in`
  line `writing which the court may think relevant to the issue, and the Magistrate or officer executing the`
  line `commission shall examine the witness upon such interrogatories.`
  line
  line `(2) The prosecutor and the accused person may appear before such magistrate or officer by counsel or`
  line `except in the case of an accused person in custody, in person, and may examine, cross-examine and reexamine,`
  line `as the case may be, the said witness.`
  line
  line `(3) After a commission issued under section 136 has been duly executed, it shall be returned, together`
  line `with the deposition of the witness examined thereunder to the Chief Legal Adviser.`
  line
  line `(4) On receipt of a commission and deposition returned under sub-section (3) the Chief Legal Adviser`
  line `shall forward the same to the court at whose instance the commission was issued or, if such court has`
  line `been dissolved, to any other court convened for the trial of the accused person, and the commission, the`
  line `return thereto and the deposition shall be open to inspection by the prosecutor and the accused person,`
  line `and may, subject to all just exceptions, be read in evidence in the case by either the prosecutor or the`
  line `accused, and shall form part of the proceedings of the court.`
  line
  line `(5) In every case in which a commission is issued under section 136 the trial may be adjourned for a`
  line `specified time reasonably sufficient for the execution and return of the commission.`
obj_root_law_sections_137_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_138:
  sectionId (28982)
  sectionNo (138)
  orderNo 138
  title `Conviction of offence not charged.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_138_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_138_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=28982&sectionno=138&orderno=138&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_138_content:
  string
  line `(1) A person charged before a court-martial with`
  line `desertion may be found guilty of attempting to desert or of being absent without leave.`
  line
  line `(2) A person charged before a court-martial with attempting to desert may be found guilty of being`
  line `absent without leave.`
  line
  line `(3) A person charged before a court-martial with using criminal force-may be found guilty of assault.`
  line
  line `(4) A person charged before a court-martial with using threatening language may be found guilty of`
  line `using insubordinate language.`
  line
  line `(5) A person charged before a court-martial with any one of the offences specified in clauses (a), (b),`
  line `(c) and (d) of section 52 may be found guilty of any other of these offences with which he might have`
  line `been charged.`
  line
  line `(6) A person charged before a court-martial with an offence punishable under section 71 may be`
  line `found guilty of any other offence of which he might have been found guilty if the provisions of the Code`
  line `of Criminal Procedure, 1898 (5 of 1898), were applicable.`
  line
  line `(7) A person charged before a court-martial with any offence under this Act may on failure of proof`
  line `of an offence having been committed in circumstances involving a more severe punishment, be found`
  line `guilty of the same offence as having been committed in circumstances involving a less severe`
  line punishment.
  line
  line `(8) A person charged before a court-martial with any offence under this Act may be found guilty of`
  line `having attempted or abetted the commission of that offence, although the attempt or abetment is not`
  line `separately charged.`
obj_root_law_sections_138_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_139:
  sectionId (28983)
  sectionNo (139)
  orderNo 139
  title `Presumption as to signatures.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_139_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_139_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=28983&sectionno=139&orderno=139&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_139_content:
  string
  line `In any proceeding under this Act, any application, certificate,`
  line `warrant, reply or other document purporting to be signed by an officer in the service of the Government`
  line `shall, on production, be presumed to have been duly signed by the person by whom and in the character in`
  line `which it purports to have been signed, until the contrary is shown.`
obj_root_law_sections_139_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_140:
  sectionId (28984)
  sectionNo (140)
  orderNo 140
  title `Enrolment paper.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_140_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_140_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=28984&sectionno=140&orderno=140&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_140_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any enrolment paper purporting to be signed by an enrolling officer`
  line `shall, in proceedings under this Act, be evidence of the person enrolled having given the answers to`
  line `questions which he is therein represented as having given.`
  line
  line `(2) The enrolment of such person may be proved by the production of the original or a copy of his`
  line `enrolment paper purporting to be certified to be a true copy by the officer having the custody of the`
  line `enrolment paper.`
obj_root_law_sections_140_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_141:
  sectionId (28985)
  sectionNo (141)
  orderNo 141
  title `Presumption as to certain documents.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_141_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 19 of 1955, s. 2 and the Schedule, for the "Commander-in Chief" (w.e.f. 7-5-1955).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=28985&sectionno=141&orderno=141&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_141_content:
  string
  line `(1) A letter, return or other document respecting the`
  line `service of any person in, or the cashiering, dismissal or discharge of any person from, any portion of the`
  line `Air Force, or respecting the circumstance of any person not having served in, or belonged to, any portion`
  line `of the Forces, if purporting to be signed by or on behalf of the Central Government or^1[the Chief of the`
  line `Air Staff], or by any prescribed officer, shall be evidence of the facts stated in such letter, return or other`
  line document.
  line
  line `(2) An Army, Navy or Air Force List or Gazette purporting to be published by authority shall be`
  line `evidence of the status and rank of the officers or warrant officers therein mentioned, and of any`
  line `appointment held by them and of the unit or branch of the services to which they belong.`
  line
  line `(3) Where a record is made in any service book in pursuance of this Act or of any rules made`
  line `thereunder or otherwise in pursuance of air force duty and purports to be signed by the commanding`
  line `officer or by the officer whose duty it is to make such record, such record shall be evidence of the facts`
  line `therein stated.`
  line
  line `(4) A copy of any record in any service book purporting to be certified to be a true copy by the officer`
  line `having custody of such book shall be evidence of such record.`
  line
  line `(5) Where any person subject to this Act is being tried on a charge of desertion or of absence without`
  line `leave, and such person has surrendered himself into the custody of any officer or other person subject to`
  line `this Act, or any portion of the Air Force, or has been apprehended by such officer or person, a certificate`
  line `purporting to be signed by such officer, or by the commanding officer of that portion of the Air Force, or`
  line `by the commanding officer of the unit, or detachment to which such person belongs, as the case may be,`
  line `and stating the fact, date and place of such surrender or apprehension, and the manner in which he was`
  line `dressed, shall be evidence of the matters so stated.`
  line
  line `(6) Where any person subject to this Act is being tried on a charge of desertion or of absence without`
  line `leave, and such person has surrendered himself into the custody of or has been apprehended by, a police`
  line `officer nor below the rank of an officer-in-charge of a police station, a certificate purporting to be signed`
  line `by such police officer and stating the fact, date and place if such surrender or apprehension and the`
  line `manner in which he was dressed shall be evidence of the matters so stated.`
  line
  line `(7) Any document purporting to be a report under the hand of any Chemical Examiner or Assistant`
  line `Chemical Examiner to Government upon any matter or thing duly submitted to him for examination or`
  line `analysis and report may be used as evidence in any proceeding under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_142:
  sectionId (28986)
  sectionNo (142)
  orderNo 142
  title `Reference by accused to Government officer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_142_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_142_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=28986&sectionno=142&orderno=142&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_142_content:
  string
  line `(1) If at any trial for desertion or absence`
  line `without leave, overstaying leave or not rejoining when warned for service, the person tried states in his`
  line `defence any sufficient or reasonable excuse for his unauthorised absence and refers in support thereof to`
  line `any officer in the service, of the Government, or if it appears that any such officer is likely to prove or`
  line `disprove the said statement in the defence, the court shall address such officer and adjourn the`
  line `proceedings until his reply is received.`
  line
  line `(2) The written reply of any officer so referred to shall, if signed by him, be received in evidence and`
  line `have the same effect as if made on oath before the court.`
  line
  line `(3) If the court is dissolved before the receipt of such reply, or if the court omits to comply with the`
  line `provisions of this section, the convening officer may, at his discretion, annul the proceedings and order a`
  line `fresh trial.`
obj_root_law_sections_142_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_143:
  sectionId (28987)
  sectionNo (143)
  orderNo 143
  title `Evidence of previous convictions and general character`
  content obj_root_law_sections_143_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_143_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=28987&sectionno=143&orderno=143&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_143_content:
  string
  line `(1) When any person subject to`
  line `this Act has been convicted by a court-martial of any offence, such court-martial may inquire into and`
  line `receive and record evidence of any previous convictions of such person, either by a court-martial or by a`
  line `criminal court or any previous award of punishment under section 82 or section 86 and may further`
  line `enquire into and record the general character of such person and such other matters as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) Evidence received under this section may be either oral, or in the shape of entries in, or certified`
  line `extracts from, court-martial books or other official records, and it shall not be necessary to give notice`
  line `before trial to the person tried that evidence as to his previous convictions or character will be received.`
obj_root_law_sections_143_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_144:
  sectionId (28988)
  sectionNo (144)
  orderNo 144
  title `Lunacy of accused`
  content obj_root_law_sections_144_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_144_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=28988&sectionno=144&orderno=144&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_144_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whenever, in the course of a trial by a court-martial, it appears to the`
  line `court that the person charged is by reason of unsoundness of mind incapable of making his defence, or`
  line `that he committed the act alleged but was by reason of unsoundness of mind incapable of knowing the`
  line `nature of the act or knowing that it was wrong or contrary to law, the court shall record a finding`
  line accordingly.
  line
  line `(2) The presiding officer of the court shall forthwith report the case to the confirming officer.`
  line `(3) The confirming officer to whom the case is reported under sub-section (2) may, if he does not`
  line `confirm the finding, take steps to have the accused person tried by the same or another court-martial for`
  line `the offence with which he was charged.`
  line
  line `(4) A confirming officer confirming a finding in any case so reported to him under sub-section (2)`
  line `shall order the accused person to be kept in custody in the prescribed manner and shall report the case for`
  line `the orders of the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(5) On receipt of a report under sub-section (4) the Central Government may order the accused person`
  line `to be detained in a lunatic asylum or other suitable place of safe custody.`
obj_root_law_sections_144_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_145:
  sectionId (28989)
  sectionNo (145)
  orderNo 145
  title `Subsequent fitness of lunatic accused for trial.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_145_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_145_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=28989&sectionno=145&orderno=145&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_145_content:
  string
  line `Where any accused person, having been`
  line `found by reason of unsoundness of mind to be incapable of making his defence, is in custody or under`
  line `detention under section 144, the officer commanding a unit or detachment within the area of whose`
  line `command the accused is in custody or is detained, or any other officer prescribed in this behalf, may. --`
  line
  line `(a) If such person is in custody under sub-section (4) of section 144, on the report of a medical`
  line `officer that he is capable of making his defence, or`
  line
  line `(b) if such person is detained in a jail under sub-section (5) of section 144, on a certificate of the`
  line `Inspector-General of Prisons and if such person is detained in a lunatic asylum under the said subsection`
  line `on a certificate of any two or more of the visitors of such asylum that he is capable of making`
  line `his defence,`
  line
  line `take steps to have such person tried by the same or another court-martial for the offence with which he`
  line `was originally charged, or, if the offence is a civil offence, by a criminal court.`
obj_root_law_sections_145_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_146:
  sectionId (28990)
  sectionNo (146)
  orderNo 146
  title `Transmission to Central Government of orders under section 145.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_146_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_146_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=28990&sectionno=146&orderno=146&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_146_content:
  string
  line `A copy of every order`
  line `made by an officer under section 145 for the trial of the accused shall forthwith be sent to the Central`
  line Government.
obj_root_law_sections_146_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_147:
  sectionId (28991)
  sectionNo (147)
  orderNo 147
  title `Release of lunatic accused.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_147_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_147_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=28991&sectionno=147&orderno=147&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_147_content:
  string
  line `Where any person is in custody under sub-section (4) of`
  line `section 144 or under detention under sub-section (5) of that section.--`
  line
  line `(a) if such person is in custody under the said sub-section (4), on the report of a medical officer, or`
  line
  line `(b) if such person is detained under the said sub-section (5), on a certificate from any of the`
  line `authorities mentioned in clause (b) of section 145 that, in the judgment of such officer or authority such`
  line `person may be released without danger of his doing injury to himself or to any other person,`
  line
  line `the Central Government may order that such person be released, or detained in custody, or transferred to a`
  line `public lunatic asylum if he has not already been sent to such an asylum.`
obj_root_law_sections_147_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_148:
  sectionId (28992)
  sectionNo (148)
  orderNo 148
  title `Delivery of lunatic accused to relatives`
  content obj_root_law_sections_148_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_148_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=28992&sectionno=148&orderno=148&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_148_content:
  string
  line `Where any relative or friend of any person who is in`
  line `custody under sub-section (4) of section 144 or under detention under sub-section (5) of that section`
  line `desires that he should be delivered to his care and custody, the Central Government may upon application`
  line `by such relative or friend and on his giving security to the satisfaction of that Government that the person`
  line `delivered shall be properly taken care of and prevented from doing injury to himself or any other person,`
  line `and be produced for the inspection of such officer, and at such times and places, as the Central`
  line `Government may direct, order such person to be delivered to such relative or friend.`
obj_root_law_sections_148_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_149:
  sectionId (28993)
  sectionNo (149)
  orderNo 149
  title `Order for custody and disposal of property pending trial`
  content obj_root_law_sections_149_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_149_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=28993&sectionno=149&orderno=149&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_149_content:
  string
  line `When any property regarding`
  line `which any offence appears to have been committed, or which appears to have been used for the`
  line `commission of any offence, is produced before a court-martial during a trial, the court may make such`
  line `order as it thinks fit for the proper custody of such property pending the conclusion of the trial, and if the`
  line `property is subject to speedy or natural decay may, after recording such evidence as it thinks necessary,`
  line `order it to be sold or otherwise disposed of.`
obj_root_law_sections_149_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_150:
  sectionId (28994)
  sectionNo (150)
  orderNo 150
  title `Order for disposal of property regarding which offence is committed`
  content obj_root_law_sections_150_content
  footnotes `1.Subs. by A.O.(No.3), 1956, for "a Part B State" (w.e.f. 7-5-1955).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=28994&sectionno=150&orderno=150&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_150_content:
  string
  line `(1) After the`
  line `conclusion of a trial before any court-martial, the court or the officer confirming the finding or sentence`
  line `of such court-martial or any authority superior to such officer, may make such order as it or he thinks fit`
  line `for the disposal by destruction, confiscation, delivery to any person, claiming to be entitled to possession`
  line `thereof, or otherwise of any property or document produced before the Court or in its custody, or regarding`
  line `which any offence appears to have been committed or which has been used for the commission of any`
  line offence.
  line
  line `(2) Where any order has been made under sub-section (1) in respect of property regarding which an`
  line `offence appears to have been committed, a copy of such order signed and certified by the authority`
  line `making the same may, whether the trial was held within India or not, be sent to a magistrate within whose`
  line `jurisdiction such property for the time being is situated, and such Magistrate shall thereupon cause the`
  line `order to be carried into effect as if it were an order passed by him under the provisions of the Code of`
  line `Criminal Procedure, 1898 (5 of 1898), or any corresponding law in force in ^1[the State of Jammu and`
  line Kashmir].
  line
  line `(3) In this section the term "property" includes, in the case of property regarding which an offence`
  line `appears to have been committed, not only such property as has been originally in the possession or under`
  line `the control of any person, but also any property into or for which the same may have been converted or`
  line `exchanged, and anything acquired by such conversion or exchange whether immediately or otherwise.`
obj_root_law_sections_151:
  sectionId (28995)
  sectionNo (151)
  orderNo 151
  title `Powers of courts-martial when certain offences are committed by persons not subject to this Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_151_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_151_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=28995&sectionno=151&orderno=151&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_151_content:
  string
  line `Any trial by a court-martial under the provisions of this Act shall be deemed to be a judicial`
  line `proceeding within the meaning of sections 193 and 228 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860), and the`
  line `court-martial shall be deemed to be a Court within the meaning of sections 480 and 482 of the Code of`
  line `Criminal Procedure, 1898 (5 of 1898).`
obj_root_law_sections_151_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_152:
  sectionId (28996)
  sectionNo (152)
  orderNo 152
  title `Finding and sentence not valid, unless confirmed.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_152_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_152_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=28996&sectionno=152&orderno=152&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_152_content:
  string
  line `No finding or sentence of a general,`
  line `district or summary general court-martial shall be valid except so far as it may be confirmed as provided`
  line `by this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_152_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_153:
  sectionId (28997)
  sectionNo (153)
  orderNo 153
  title `Power to confirm finding and sentence of general court-martial.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_153_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_153_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=28997&sectionno=153&orderno=153&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_153_content:
  string
  line `The findings and`
  line `sentences of general courts-martial may be confirmed by the Central Government, or by any officer`
  line `empowered in this behalf by warrant of the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_153_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_154:
  sectionId (28998)
  sectionNo (154)
  orderNo 154
  title `Power to confirm finding and sentence of district court-martial.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_154_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_154_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=28998&sectionno=154&orderno=154&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_154_content:
  string
  line `The findings and`
  line `sentences of district court-martial may be confirmed by any officer having power to convene a general`
  line `court-martial or by any officer empowered in this behalf by warrant of such officer.`
obj_root_law_sections_154_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_155:
  sectionId (28999)
  sectionNo (155)
  orderNo 155
  title `Limitation of powers of confirming authority`
  content obj_root_law_sections_155_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_155_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=28999&sectionno=155&orderno=155&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_155_content:
  string
  line `A warrant issued under section 153 or`
  line `section 154 may contain such restrictions, reservations or conditions as the authority issuing it may think`
  line fit.
obj_root_law_sections_155_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_156:
  sectionId (29000)
  sectionNo (156)
  orderNo 156
  title `Power to confirm finding and sentence of summary general courts- martial.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_156_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_156_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=29000&sectionno=156&orderno=156&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_156_content:
  string
  line `The findings`
  line `and sentences of summary general courts-martial may be confirmed by the convening officer or if he so`
  line `directs, by an authority superior to him.`
obj_root_law_sections_156_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_157:
  sectionId (29001)
  sectionNo (157)
  orderNo 157
  title `Power of confirming authority to mitigate, remit or commute sentences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_157_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_157_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=29001&sectionno=157&orderno=157&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_157_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to`
  line `such restrictions, reservations or conditions as may be contained in any warrant issued under section 153`
  line `or section 154 and to the provisions of sub-sections (2) and (3), a confirming authority may, when`
  line `confirming the sentence of a court-martial, mitigate or remit the punishment thereby awarded, or`
  line `commute that punishment for any punishment or punishments lower in the scale laid down in section 73.`
  line
  line `(2) A sentence of transportation shall not be commuted for a sentence of imprisonment or detention`
  line `for a term exceeding the term of transportation awarded by the court.`
  line
  line `(3) A sentence of imprisonment shall not be commuted for a sentence of detention for a term`
  line `exceeding the term of imprisonment awarded by the court.`
obj_root_law_sections_157_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_158:
  sectionId (29002)
  sectionNo (158)
  orderNo 158
  title `Confirming of findings and sentences on board a ship.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_158_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_158_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=29002&sectionno=158&orderno=158&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_158_content:
  string
  line `When any person subject to this Act`
  line `is tried and sentenced by a court-martial while on board a ship, the finding and sentence so far as not`
  line `confirmed and executed on board the ship, may be confirmed and executed in like manner as if such`
  line `person had been tried at the port of disembarkation.`
obj_root_law_sections_158_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_159:
  sectionId (29003)
  sectionNo (159)
  orderNo 159
  title `Revision of finding or sentence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_159_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_159_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=29003&sectionno=159&orderno=159&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_159_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any finding or sentence of a court-martial may be once`
  line `revised by order of the confirming authority and on such revision, the court, if so directed by the`
  line `confirming authority, may take additional evidence.`
  line
  line `(2) The court, on revision, shall consist of the same officers as were present when the original`
  line `decision was passed, unless any of those officers are unavoidably absent.`
  line
  line `(3) In case of such unavoidable absence the cause thereof shall be duly certified in the proceedings,`
  line `and the court shall proceed with the revision, provided that, if a general court-martial, it still consists of`
  line `five officers, or, if a summary general or district court- martial, of three officers.`
obj_root_law_sections_159_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_160:
  sectionId (29004)
  sectionNo (160)
  orderNo 160
  title `Alteration of finding or sentence in certain cases`
  content obj_root_law_sections_160_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_160_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=29004&sectionno=160&orderno=160&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_160_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where a finding of guilty by a courtmartial,`
  line `which has been confirmed, is found for any reason to be invalid or cannot be supported by the`
  line `evidence, the authority which would have had power under section 177 to commute the punishment awarded by the sentence, if the finding had been valid, may substitute a new finding and pass a sentence`
  line `for the offence specified or involved in such finding:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such substitution shall be made unless such finding could have been validly made by`
  line `the court-martial on the charge and unless it appears that the court-martial must have been satisfied of the`
  line `facts establishing the offence.`
  line
  line `(2) Where a sentence passed by a court-martial which has been confirmed not being a sentence passed`
  line `in pursuance of a new finding substituted under sub-section (1), is found for any reason to be invalid, the.`
  line `authority referred to in sub-section (1) may pass a valid sentence.`
  line
  line `(3) The punishment awarded by a sentence passed under sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) shall not`
  line `be higher in the scale of punishments than, or in excess of the punishment awarded by, the sentence for`
  line `which a new sentence is substituted under this section.`
  line
  line `(4) Any finding substituted, or any sentence passed, under this section shall for the purposes of this`
  line `Act and the rules made thereunder have effect as if it were a finding or sentence, as the case may be, of a`
  line court-martial.
obj_root_law_sections_160_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_161:
  sectionId (29005)
  sectionNo (161)
  orderNo 161
  title `Remedy against order, finding or sentence of court-martial.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_161_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 19 of 1955, s. 2 and the Schedule, for "the Commander-in-Chief" (w.e.f. 7-5-1955).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=29005&sectionno=161&orderno=161&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_161_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person subject to this`
  line `Act who considers himself aggrieved by any order passed by a court-martial may present a petition to the`
  line `officer or authority empowered to confirm any finding or sentence of such court-martial, and the`
  line `confirming authority may take such steps as may be considered necessary to satisfy itself as to the`
  line `correctness, legality or propriety of the order passed or as to the regularity of any proceeding to which the`
  line `order relates.`
  line
  line `(2) Any person subject to this Act who considers himself aggrieved by a finding or sentence of a`
  line `court-martial which has been confirmed, may present a petition to the Central Government, ^1[the Chief of`
  line `the Air Staff] or any prescribed officer superior in command to the one who confirmed such finding or`
  line `sentence, and the Central Government, ^1[the Chief of the Air Staff] or other officer, as the case may be,`
  line `may pass such order thereon as it or he thinks fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_162:
  sectionId (29006)
  sectionNo (162)
  orderNo 162
  title `Annulment of proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_162_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 19 of 1955, s. 2 and the Schedule, for "the Commander-in-Chief" (w.e.f. 7-5-1955).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=29006&sectionno=162&orderno=162&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_162_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government, ^1[the Chief of the Air Staff] or any`
  line `prescribed officer may annul the proceedings of any court-martial on the ground that they are illegal or`
  line unjust.
obj_root_law_sections_163:
  sectionId (29007)
  sectionNo (163)
  orderNo 163
  title `Form of sentence of death`
  content obj_root_law_sections_163_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_163_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=29007&sectionno=163&orderno=163&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_163_content:
  string
  line `In awarding a sentence of death, a court-martial shall, in its`
  line `discretion, direct that the offender shall suffer death by being hanged by the neck until he be dead or shall`
  line `suffer death by being shot to death.`
obj_root_law_sections_163_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_164:
  sectionId (29008)
  sectionNo (164)
  orderNo 164
  title `Commencement of sentence of transportation or imprisonment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_164_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_164_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=29008&sectionno=164&orderno=164&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_164_content:
  string
  line `Whenever any person is`
  line `sentenced by a court-martial under this Act to transportation, imprisonment or detention the term of his`
  line `sentence shall, whether it has been revised or not, be reckoned to commence on the day on which the`
  line `original proceedings were signed by the presiding officer.`
obj_root_law_sections_164_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_165:
  sectionId (29009)
  sectionNo (165)
  orderNo 165
  title `Execution of sentence of transportation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_165_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_165_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=29009&sectionno=165&orderno=165&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_165_content:
  string
  line `Whenever any sentence of transportation is passed`
  line `under this Act or whenever any sentence of death be commuted to transportation, the commanding officer`
  line `of the person under sentence or such other officer as may be prescribed shall forward a warrant in the`
  line `prescribed form to the officer-in-charge of the civil prison in which such person is to be confined and`
  line `shall arrange for his dispatch to such prison with the warrant.`
obj_root_law_sections_165_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_166:
  sectionId (29010)
  sectionNo (166)
  orderNo 166
  title `Execution of sentence of imprisonment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_166_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_166_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=29010&sectionno=166&orderno=166&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_166_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whenever any sentence of imprisonment is`
  line `passed under this Act or whenever any sentence of death or transportation is commuted to imprisonment,`
  line `the confirming officer or such other officer as may be prescribed, shall, save as otherwise provided in`
  line `sub-sections (3) and (4), direct either that the sentence shall be carried out by confinement in a military or`
  line `air force prison or that it shall be carried out by confinement in a civil prison.`
  line
  line `(2) When a direction has been made under sub-section (1) the commanding officer of the person`
  line `under sentence or such other officer as may be prescribed shall forward a warrant in the prescribed form`
  line `to the officer-in-charge of the prison in which such person is to be confined and shall arrange for his`
  line `dispatch to such prison with the warrant.`
  line
  line `(3) In the case of a sentence of imprisonment for a period not exceeding three months, the officers`
  line `referred to in sub-section (1) may direct that the sentence shall be carried out by confinement in air force`
  line `custody instead of in a civil or military or air force prison.`
  line
  line `(4) On active service, a sentence of imprisonment may be carried out by confinement in such place as`
  line `the officer commanding the forces in the field may from time to time, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_166_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_167:
  sectionId (29011)
  sectionNo (167)
  orderNo 167
  title `Temporary custody of offender.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_167_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_167_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=29011&sectionno=167&orderno=167&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_167_content:
  string
  line `Where a sentence of transportation or imprisonment is`
  line `directed to be undergone in a civil prison, the offender may be kept in military or air force custody or in`
  line `any other fit place, till such time as it is possible to send him to a civil prison.`
obj_root_law_sections_167_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_168:
  sectionId (29012)
  sectionNo (168)
  orderNo 168
  title `Execution of sentence of imprisonment in special cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_168_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_168_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=29012&sectionno=168&orderno=168&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_168_content:
  string
  line `Whenever, in the opinion of an air`
  line `or other officer commanding a group, any sentence or portion of a sentence of imprisonment cannot for`
  line `special reasons, conveniently be carried out in a military or air force prison or in air force custody in`
  line `accordance with the provisions of section 166 such officer may direct that such sentence or portion of`
  line `sentence shall be carried out by confinement in any civil prison or other fit place.`
obj_root_law_sections_168_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_169:
  sectionId (29013)
  sectionNo (169)
  orderNo 169
  title `Conveyance of prisoner from place to place.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_169_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_169_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=29013&sectionno=169&orderno=169&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_169_content:
  string
  line `A person under sentence of transportation or`
  line `imprisonment may, during his conveyance from place to place, or when on board a ship, aircraft, or`
  line `otherwise, be subjected to such restraint as is necessary for his safe conduct and removal.`
obj_root_law_sections_169_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_170:
  sectionId (29014)
  sectionNo (170)
  orderNo 170
  title `Execution of sentence of detention.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_170_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_170_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=29014&sectionno=170&orderno=170&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_170_content:
  string
  line `Whenever any sentence of detention is passed under this`
  line `Act, or whenever any sentence of death, transportation or imprisonment is commuted to detention, the`
  line `sentence shall be carried out by detaining the offender in any military or air force detention barracks,`
  line `detention cells or other military or air force custody; and when the sentence is to be carried out by`
  line `detention in any military or air force detention barracks, the commanding officer of the person under`
  line `sentence or such other officer as may be prescribed shall forward a warrant in the prescribed form to the`
  line `officer-in-charge of the detention barracks in which the person under sentence is to be detained and shall`
  line `forward the person under sentence to such detention barracks with the warrant.`
obj_root_law_sections_170_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_171:
  sectionId (29015)
  sectionNo (171)
  orderNo 171
  title `Communication of certain orders to prison officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_171_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_171_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=29015&sectionno=171&orderno=171&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_171_content:
  string
  line `Whenever an order if duly made under`
  line `this Act setting aside or varying any sentence, order or warrant under which any person is confined in a`
  line `civil, military or air force prison or detained in a military or air force detention barracks, a warrant in`
  line `accordance with such order shall be forwarded by the officer making the order, or his staff officer, or such`
  line `other person as may be prescribed, to the officer in charge of the prison or detention barracks in which`
  line `such person is confined.`
obj_root_law_sections_171_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_172:
  sectionId (29016)
  sectionNo (172)
  orderNo 172
  title `Execution of sentence of fine`
  content obj_root_law_sections_172_content
  footnotes `1. Subs by the A.O.(No. 3), 1956, for "a Part B State" (w.e.f. 7-5-1955).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=29016&sectionno=172&orderno=172&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_172_content:
  string
  line `When a sentence of fine is imposed by a court-martial under`
  line `section 71 whether the trial was held within India or not, a copy of such sentence, signed and certified by`
  line `the confirming officer may be sent to any magistrate in India, and such magistrate shall thereupon cause`
  line `the fine to be recovered in accordance with the provisions of the Code of Criminal Procedure,`
  line `1898 (5 of 1898), or any corresponding law in force in ^1[the State of Jammu and Kashmir], for the levy of`
  line `fines as if were a sentence of fine imposed by such Magistrate.`
obj_root_law_sections_173:
  sectionId (29017)
  sectionNo (173)
  orderNo 173
  title `Establishment and regulation of air force prisons.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_173_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_173_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=29017&sectionno=173&orderno=173&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_173_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may set apart`
  line `any building or part of a building, or any place under its control, as an air force prison or detention`
  line `barracks for the confinement of persons sentenced to imprisonment or detention under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_173_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_174:
  sectionId (29018)
  sectionNo (174)
  orderNo 174
  title `Informality or error in the order or warrants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_174_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_174_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=29018&sectionno=174&orderno=174&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_174_content:
  string
  line `Whenever a person is sentenced to`
  line `transportation, imprisonment or detention under this Act, and is undergoing the sentence in any place or`
  line `manner in which he might be confined under a lawful order or warrant in pursuance of this Act, the`
  line `confinement of such person shall not be deemed to be illegal only by reason of any informality or error in`
  line `or as respects the order, warrant or other document, or the authority by which, or in pursuance whereof`
  line `such person was brought into or is confined in any such place, and any such order, warrant or document`
  line `may be amended accordingly.`
obj_root_law_sections_174_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_175:
  sectionId (29019)
  sectionNo (175)
  orderNo 175
  title `Power to make rules in respect of prisons and prisoners.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_175_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_175_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=29019&sectionno=175&orderno=175&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_175_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may`
  line `make rules providing.--(a) for the government, management and regulation of air force prisons and`
  line `detention barracks;`
  line
  line `(b) for the appointment, removal and power of inspectors, visitors, governors and officers thereof;`
  line
  line `(c) for the labour of prisoners undergoing confinement therein, and for enabling such prisoners`
  line `or, persons to earn by special industry and good conduct; a remission of a portion of their sentence;`
  line
  line `(d) for the safe custody of such prisoners or persons and the maintenance of discipline among`
  line `them and the punishment, by personal correction, restraint or otherwise, of offences committed by`
  line them;
  line
  line `(e) for the application to air force prisons or detention barracks of any of the provisions of the`
  line `Prisons Act, 1894 (9 of 1894), relating to the duties of officers of prisons and the punishment of`
  line `persons not being prisoners;`
  line
  line `(f) for the admission into any prison, at proper times and subject, to proper restrictions, of`
  line `person's with whom prisoners may desire to communicate and for the consultation by prisoners under`
  line `trial' with their legal advisers without the presence as far as possible of any third party within hearing`
  line distance.
obj_root_law_sections_175_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_176:
  sectionId (29020)
  sectionNo (176)
  orderNo 176
  title `Restriction of rule-making power in respect to corporal punishment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_176_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_176_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=29020&sectionno=176&orderno=176&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_176_content:
  string
  line `Rules made under`
  line `section 175 shall not authorise corporal punishment to be inflicted for any offence, nor render the`
  line `imprisonment more severe than it is under any law for the time being in force relating to civil prisons in`
  line India.
obj_root_law_sections_176_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_177:
  sectionId (29021)
  sectionNo (177)
  orderNo 177
  title `Pardon and remission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_177_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 19 of 1955, s. 2 and the Schedule, for "the Commander-in-Chief" (w.e.f. 7-5-1955).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=29021&sectionno=177&orderno=177&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_177_content:
  string
  line `When any person subject to this Act has been convicted by a courtmartial`
  line `of any offence, the Central Government, ^1[the Chief of the Air Staff], an air or other officer`
  line `commanding a group or the prescribed officer, may--`
  line
  line `(a) either with or without conditions which the person sentenced accepts, pardon the person or`
  line `remit the whole or any part of the punishment awarded; or`
  line
  line `(b) mitigate the punishment awarded; or`
  line
  line `(c) commute such punishment for any less punishment or punishments mentioned in this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that a sentence of transportation shall not be commuted for a sentence of imprisonment`
  line `for a term exceeding the term of transportation awarded by the court; and a sentence of imprisonment`
  line `shall not be commuted for a sentence of detention for a term exceeding the term of imprisonment so`
  line awarded;
  line
  line `(d) either with or without conditions which the person sentenced accepts, release the person on`
  line parole.
obj_root_law_sections_178:
  sectionId (29022)
  sectionNo (178)
  orderNo 178
  title `Cancellation of conditional pardon, release on parole or remission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_178_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_178_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=29022&sectionno=178&orderno=178&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_178_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any condition on`
  line `which a person has been pardoned or released on parole or a punishment has been remitted is, in the`
  line `opinion of the authority which granted the pardon, release or remission, not fulfilled, such authority may`
  line `cancel the pardon, release or remission, and thereupon the sentence of, the court shall be carried into`
  line `effect as if such pardon, release or remission had not been granted.`
  line
  line `(2) A person whose sentence of transportation, imprisonment or detention is carried into effect under`
  line `the provisions of sub-section (1) shall undergo only the unexpired portion of his sentence.`
obj_root_law_sections_178_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_179:
  sectionId (29023)
  sectionNo (179)
  orderNo 179
  title `Reduction of warrant officer or non-commissioned officer`
  content obj_root_law_sections_179_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_179_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=29023&sectionno=179&orderno=179&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_179_content:
  string
  line `When under the provisions of`
  line `section 79 a warrant officer or a non-commissioned officer is deemed to be reduced to the ranks, such`
  line `reduction shall, for the purpose of section 177, be treated as a punishment awarded by a sentence of a`
  line court-martial.
obj_root_law_sections_179_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_180:
  sectionId (29024)
  sectionNo (180)
  orderNo 180
  title `Suspension of sentence of transportation, imprisonment or detention.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_180_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 19 of 1955, s. 2 and the Schedule "the Commander-in-Chief" (w.e.f. 7-5-1955).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=29024&sectionno=180&orderno=180&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_180_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where a person`
  line `subject to this Act is sentenced by a court-martial to transportation, imprisonment or detention, the`
  line `Central Government, ^1[the Chief of the Air Staff] or any officer empowered to convene a general or a`
  line `summary general court-martial may suspend the sentence whether or not the offender has already been`
  line `committed to prison or to air force custody.`
  line
  line `(2) The authority or officer specified in sub-section (1) may in the case of an offender so sentenced`
  line `direct that, until the orders of such authority or officer have been obtained, the offender shall not be`
  line `committed to prison or to air force custody.`
  line
  line `(3) The powers conferred by sub-sections (1) and (2) may be exercised in the case of any such`
  line `sentence which has been confirmed, reduced or commuted.`
obj_root_law_sections_181:
  sectionId (29025)
  sectionNo (181)
  orderNo 181
  title `Orders pending suspension.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_181_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_181_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=29025&sectionno=181&orderno=181&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_181_content:
  string
  line `A confirming officer may, when confirming any sentence`
  line `referred to in section 180, direct that the offender be not committed to prison or to air force custody until`
  line `the orders of the authority or officer specified in section 180 have been obtained.`
obj_root_law_sections_181_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_182:
  sectionId (29026)
  sectionNo (182)
  orderNo 182
  title `Release on suspension.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_182_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_182_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=29026&sectionno=182&orderno=182&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_182_content:
  string
  line `Where a sentence is suspended under section 180, the offender shall`
  line `forthwith be released from custody.`
obj_root_law_sections_182_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_183:
  sectionId (29027)
  sectionNo (183)
  orderNo 183
  title `Computation of period of suspension.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_183_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_183_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=29027&sectionno=183&orderno=183&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_183_content:
  string
  line `Any period during which the sentence is under`
  line `suspension shall be reckoned as part of the term of such sentence.`
obj_root_law_sections_183_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_184:
  sectionId (29028)
  sectionNo (184)
  orderNo 184
  title `Order after suspension.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_184_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_184_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=29028&sectionno=184&orderno=184&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_184_content:
  string
  line `The authority or officer specified in section 180, at any time while a`
  line `sentence is suspended, order--`
  line
  line `(a) that the offender be committed to undergo the unexpired portion of the sentence, or`
  line
  line `(b) that the sentence be remitted.`
obj_root_law_sections_184_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_185:
  sectionId (29029)
  sectionNo (185)
  orderNo 185
  title `Reconsideration of case after suspension`
  content obj_root_law_sections_185_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_185_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=29029&sectionno=185&orderno=185&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_185_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where a sentence has been suspended, the case`
  line `may at any time, and shall, at intervals of not more than four months, be reconsidered by the authority or`
  line `officer specified in section 180, or by any air or other officer not below the rank of squadron leader duly`
  line `authorised by the authority or officer specified in section 180.`
  line
  line `(2) Where on such reconsideration by the officer so authorised it appears to him that the conduct of`
  line `the offender since his conviction has been such as to justify a remission of the sentence, he shall refer the`
  line `matter to the authority or officer specified in section 180.`
obj_root_law_sections_185_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_186:
  sectionId (29030)
  sectionNo (186)
  orderNo 186
  title `Fresh sentence after suspension.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_186_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_186_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=29030&sectionno=186&orderno=186&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_186_content:
  string
  line `Where an offender, while a sentence on him is suspended`
  line `under this Act, is sentenced for any other offence, them--`
  line
  line `(a) if the further sentence is also suspended under this Act, the two sentences shall run`
  line concurrently;
  line
  line `(b) if the further sentence is for a period of three months or more and is not suspended under this`
  line `Act, the offender shall also be committed to prison or air force custody for the unexpired portion of`
  line `the previous sentence, but both sentences shall run concurrently; and`
  line
  line `(c) if the further sentence is for a period of less than three months and is not suspended under this`
  line `Act, the offender shall be so committed on that sentence only, and the previous sentence shall, subject`
  line `to any order which may be passed under section 184 or section 185, continue to be suspended.`
obj_root_law_sections_186_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_187:
  sectionId (29031)
  sectionNo (187)
  orderNo 187
  title `Scope of power of suspension`
  content obj_root_law_sections_187_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_187_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=29031&sectionno=187&orderno=187&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_187_content:
  string
  line `The powers conferred by sections 180 and 184 shall be in`
  line `addition to and not in derogation of, the power of mitigation, remission and commutation.`
obj_root_law_sections_187_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_188:
  sectionId (29032)
  sectionNo (188)
  orderNo 188
  title `Effect of suspension and remission on dismissal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_188_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_188_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=29032&sectionno=188&orderno=188&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_188_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where in addition to any other sentence`
  line `the punishment of dismissal has been awarded by a court-martial, and such other sentence is suspended`
  line `under section 180, then, such dismissal shall not take effect until so ordered by the authority or officer`
  line `specified in section 180.`
  line
  line `(2) If such other sentence is remitted under section 184, the punishment of dismissal shall also be`
  line remitted.
obj_root_law_sections_188_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_189:
  sectionId (29033)
  sectionNo (189)
  orderNo 189
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_189_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_189_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=29033&sectionno=189&orderno=189&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_189_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may make rules for the purpose of`
  line `carrying into effect the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the generality of the power conferred by sub-section (1), the rules made`
  line `thereunder may provide for--`
  line
  line `(a) the removal, retirement, release or discharge from the service of persons subject to this Act;`
  line
  line `(b) the amount and incidence of fines to be imposed under section 90;`
  line
  line `(c) the specification of the punishment which may be awarded as field punishments under`
  line `sections 77 and 82;`
  line
  line `(d) the assembly and procedure of courts of inquiry, the recording of summaries of evidence and`
  line `the administration of oaths or affirmations by such courts;`
  line
  line `(e) the convening and constituting of court-martial and the appointment of prosecutors at trials by`
  line court-martial;
  line
  line `(f) the adjournment, dissolution and sitting of court-martial;`
  line
  line `(g) the procedure to be observed in trials by court-martial and the appearance of legal`
  line `practitioners thereat;`
  line
  line `(h) the confirmation, revision and annulment of, and petitions against the findings and sentences`
  line `of court-martial:`
  line
  line `(i) the carrying into effect of sentences of court-martial;`
  line
  line `(j) the forms of orders to be made under the provisions of this Act relating to court-martial,`
  line `transportation, imprisonment and detention;`
  line
  line `(k) the constitution of authorities, to decide for what persons, to what amounts and in what`
  line `manner, provision should be made for dependents under section 100 and the due carrying out of such`
  line decisions;
  line
  line `(l) the relative rank of the officers, junior commissioned officers, warrant officers, petty officers`
  line `and non-commissioned officers of the regular Army, Navy and Air Force when acting together;`
  line
  line `(m) any other matter directed by this Act to be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_189_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_190:
  sectionId (29034)
  sectionNo (190)
  orderNo 190
  title `Power to make regulations`
  content obj_root_law_sections_190_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_190_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=29034&sectionno=190&orderno=190&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_190_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may make regulations for all or any of`
  line `the purposes of this Act other than those specified in section 189.`
obj_root_law_sections_190_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_191:
  sectionId (29035)
  sectionNo (191)
  orderNo 191
  title `Publication of rules and regulations in Gazette.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_191_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_191_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=29035&sectionno=191&orderno=191&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_191_content:
  string
  line `All rules and regulations made under this`
  line `Act shall be published in the Official Gazette and, on such publication, shall have effect as if enacted in`
  line `this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_191_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_191_a:
  sectionId (29036)
  sectionNo 191A
  orderNo 192
  title `Laying of rules and regulations before Parliament.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_191_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins by Act 4 of 1986, s. 2 and the Schedule ( w.e.f. 15-5-1986).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=29036&sectionno=191A&orderno=192&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_191_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[191A. Laying of rules and regulations before Parliament.--Every rule and every regulation`
  line `made under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each House of Parliament,`
  line `while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in one session or in two or`
  line `more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately following the session or the`
  line `successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification in the rule or regulation or`
  line `both Houses agree that the rule or regulation should not be made, the rule or regulation shall thereafter`
  line `have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such`
  line `modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under`
  line `that rule or regulation.]`
obj_root_law_sections_192:
  sectionId (29037)
  sectionNo (192)
  orderNo 193
  title Repealed.
  content obj_root_law_sections_192_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_192_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=29037&sectionno=192&orderno=193&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_192_content:
  string
  line `[Repeal.][Rep. by the Repealing and Amending Act, 1957 (36 of 1957), s. 2 and the First`
  line `Schedule (w.e.f.17-9-1957).`
obj_root_law_sections_192_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_193:
  sectionId (29038)
  sectionNo (193)
  orderNo 194
  title `Definition of British officer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_193_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_193_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=29038&sectionno=193&orderno=194&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_193_content:
  string
  line `(1) In this Chapter "British officer" means a person of nonIndian`
  line `domicile holding a commission in His Majesty's Air Force and serving in the Air Force.`
  line
  line `(2) The expression "superior officer" in this Act shall be deemed to include a British officer.`
obj_root_law_sections_193_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_194:
  sectionId (29039)
  sectionNo (194)
  orderNo 195
  title `Powers of British officer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_194_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_194_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980&sectionId=29039&sectionno=194&orderno=195&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00018_195045_1517807325980
obj_root_law_sections_194_content:
  string
  line `A British officer shall have all the powers conferred by this Act on`
  line `an officer of corresponding rank or holding a corresponding appointment.`
obj_root_law_sections_194_footnotes:
  string
  line
